\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 1900.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How many - could you tell me the name of the house you were born in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - I suppose it was - I couldn't tell you the right name but - it was one of the - the cottages or something belonged to }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Lawler\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  Hall you know, my father - worked on a farm and I suppose it was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How many years did you live in the house you were born in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh - not many. Not many, we couldn't have been in there very long because - we lived at another place - I think it's called 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Maylandsea Way{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} now but then I was only about three and a half. So I couldn't - couldn't have lived there for long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What was the address of this house you moved to in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}
Maylandsea{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Bay{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - oh no, I've forgotten the name of it, it's on a farm again. Yes, it was on a - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - I - that be about - four or five years I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Where did you go from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Then - we - I remember I was about seven when we moved, we moved to another place called - St Lawrence Bay. And I know 
they - we had all the furniture on the top and - they gave me the cat - hold in a bag and that slipped down in between a chair legs, the poor thing that couldn't get up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 St Lawrence Bay is a little further along?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That's near - that's on the way to Black - Bradwell. The atomic - station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How long did you live at St Lawrence Bay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh well, lots of things happened in that time. My father was the farm bailiff there. And he died and of course that alters things - altogether again. And we - then we moved - went - lived a little further down the road, in a little cottage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Still in St {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Lawrence{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Bay{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That's still - was St Lawrence Bay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How long did you stay in that cottage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well we - we stayed - I - I don't know quite how lo
ng but we stayed there for a time, and I was thirteen until I was - at least until I was thirteen and a half and - those days you could, you know, if you got so many attendances at school, you could leave a bit earlier. And - I was one of those who just a
bout got enough and scraped through. And I - well of course I had to go out then and earn me own - earn me own living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That would be about 1914 wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes, that would. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you continue to live at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No, I - had to take a little job out at - at Walthamstow. Well I was looking after two or three children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you went into service more or less did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So from 1914 you lived in Walthamstow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I didn't live in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Walthamstow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  too long because - I mean I got to the stage where - I wanted more money and they just couldn't give it me. And I left that place and - and then went to live at Shen - no, Hutton Mount. Hutton Mount, Shenfield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How long were you at this first place, a year would it be or longer or shorter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh - I don't - it'd be shorter I should think. Yes, short of a year really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about the place at Hutton Mount?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I - I went there when I was about sixteen I think. I think I was about sixteen, and I staye
d there - 1924 when I was married and that's where I was married from. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 These first moves you made as a child, do you remember why the family moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well, they was a change of farm again, you see, changing the farm as they do, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Michaealmas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  Day and - Lady Day and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Your father would look for a different situation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 He - he - well he was working for the same man but - it was another farm that he'd want him to take over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would this be promotion more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, it was on the same level but a little - probably a little bit bigger farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I've got six sisters. No brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Whereabouts do you come, are you the oldest or youngest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, I'm the third. I'm the third from the top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Could you give me their ages roughly or how many years between each one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well my eldest sister, I don't really know quite where she is but she - if she's alive still she'd be more on the eighty list. And - the n
ext one lives across here by the - and she's seven - she's seventy-two or seventy-three, I think she's still across there now. And then there was me. Yes. And - then there's a sister, oh somewhere in - North church I think she lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How old would she be roughly? How many years between you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well, that - I think there was a little - few - about four years in between - because there was a boy in the middle there but he only lived one day. He didn't live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So your next sister would be about sixty-six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, I think - I guess she would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about the two after that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well one lived in Tottenham, but I - where she got bombed during the war you know you lost count - we lost count.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 About how old would she be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh there's about two years between the whole lot. Roughly two - two years between the whole lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So that means there was seven of you in the family, six counting you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well, that boy didn't live long enough, so we just say that we were six - there were six - y
es. One - the younger sister is - still lives at Hutton. She still lives at Hutton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh Lord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you know how old he was when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, thirty-six. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Which year did he die, you said it was while you were at St Lawrence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, that was - it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That was about 1907 or 1908, do you know for sure when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I've got - marriage lines somewhere but I don't quite know where at the moment. Well I know my - 
my youngest sister - my youngest sister was - six weeks old and I don't quite exactly know how old she is at the moment. You see, I - you know - we haven't bothered about keeping up with them. And she was six years - six years old - when my mother died. S
he was six week and then - six years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So your mother died six years later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 19 - about 1942 I think. So that'll give you a little time - that'll give you a little idea of the - what the other one was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Where did your father come from originally, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Essex{\*\xmlclose}. Yes, he's {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Essex{\*\xmlclose} man. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What was his occupation, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 was she}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  always on a farm or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Always on a farm, farm bailiff. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did he ever do any other sort of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No. All farm work them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 He didn't have any other part time jobs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No, well that was a full time job really. That was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 rare}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  those days, all corn and stuff like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember your father ever being out of work, unemployed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, never. Never. He was never out of work. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Have you any idea how old your mother was when you are born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Mother - my mother come from - from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Essex{\*\xmlclose} as well. Yes, she's an 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Essex{\*\xmlclose} - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did she have any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well she was in service. Yes, yes-, she was in service. I mean, that was all there was those days to do and I expect they thought she'd got to do it. I mean there wasn't the choice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did she work at all after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well the only - the only work that she did was - what you might call - casual. We went thistle dodging if you know what that is. We picked up a few potatoes, we'd pick peas and - I don't think there was anything else that - out on the field l
ine that we did. But I know we went thistle dodging because - I went with her and they had a - have a hook thing, a rip they called it. With a point on the end, and I thought I was being handy and swung it round like that and that went in my - in my ankle
. Oh I used to love those days. Really love those days we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Who looked after the children while your mother was out in the fields?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well she - it was holidays most times, she used to take 'em with her. Oh they all had to do a little bit. We'd a
ll got our little jobs that we had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have any regular tasks to do in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh yes, yes. We - used to have - what do they call it, coconut matting. 'Cos they were brick floors. And - each one was told off on a Saturday, pick 'em
 up and pick all the cottons off them. Pick all the cotton - cottons off. The other ones had to - some of the others had to chop the wood, you know, to light the fire with. Yes, and some had got the shoes to clean. You all had our little - our little jobs
 to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How long did you carry on doing these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well until I - I - until I left home to go - you see, and into this other - but when my mother died you see there was a split. There was a split altogether. And - one - let's see, there was one
, two, three I think - the boy was fourth - but - they went - I had an aunt, when we left the farm, we had to come out of the farm, 'cos they want the man there, my uncle took it over. And - these others - smaller children went to live with her, until the
y got - old enough that they could start out on their own. But I had the next one, although I wasn't very old, she came to live with me. You know, we were like - housemaids and - things like that. So she was - I - I looked after her more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That was the youngest one when your mother died was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No, that was the - that's the next one to me. Next to - the next one to me, the next one who was ready to - you know, start our, she did more or less the same, she got enough stamps - enough }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 
attendances}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  at school so that she could get through with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So your mother would have died soon after you started in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes she did. She jolly well did. She, yes, she died on November the twenty-eighth. The sister that I had with me afterwards - 
was her birthday so I - I do know that date. Yes. Yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would that have been a year after you started service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh it was less than that. Well I started at - - Hutton. I think I went there - oh somewhere about September or - beginning of 
October, I know I wasn't there very long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 And she died just after you went to Hutton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes. Yes, I had a telegram to say, come at once. Well I didn't know - what I'd got to think. And that was jolly dark I know. And - well she used to go and help
 - out with a - sort of boarding house down at the bottom of the road, you know, to - help out her money 'cos - well there was only a - little tiny bit of pension. And there was no other sort of money coming anywhere. So she'd just go down there but - she
 got half way up the road - and that's as far as she got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They were certainly hard times then if you were left a widow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I'd like to ask you about your life at home when you were a child still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Happy. Happy days. Happy days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Could we talk about the house in St Lawrence Bay while your father was still alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That was the place you were at longest as a child wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes, that's the longest - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Could you tell me how many rooms were in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
I - they were - because that was a farm house you see, I think there was two big rooms downstairs. And I think there was two big ones, really big ones upstairs. That's about - and that place is still there and that's - yes - when they -
 I don't know whose bought it but they - you know, it's real seaside place now. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would there be a kitchen as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well there was only just this one - just the one - just the one great big place and - there was a little corner up the
 back where they had their - where the copper was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So it was all in one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes. And - well - just outside by - being a farm, just outside the back door there was a - a horses stable. So you had to go through the stables before you could get outdoors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did anyone else besides your parents and sisters live in the house, any other relatives or lodgers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 My - mother's brother, he lived with her for years and years. And he'd always lived - he - you know, he lived as one of the family.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So he was with you during practically all of your childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes. Yes he was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh no, good Lord she hadn't got nothing - she hadn't got enough for herself let alone paying anybody to help. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Washing. I don't think I shall ever forget washing. Never I don't think, we - there was a pump, when we lived in the farm there was a pump. - Pump. And - you - oh you had to pump it - oh 
that was so hard. You know, you want so much soap. But when we - when we moved to the little cottage - little further down the road, we had to get our drinking water from out of that pump.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How far did you have to carry that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh - almost up the t
op of the lane here. Quite a way. Yes, we got a couple of buckets and we had a hoop, we used to - you know, put the buckets on the side on the hoop to stop it from - swabbing all over you and that held it steady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Is this like the yoke thing the milk maids used to have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, just an ordinary wooden }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 hoop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  like you - children used to bowl. And we used to put it in between the two buckets - and a handle, and that used to keep it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That used to keep it steady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Used to hold it steady, used to 
swab a little over. But the - then when the pump - sometimes the pump wouldn't work, and there was a huge great well, you'd got to swing the bucket down the well, I wasn't much good at that. Huge great - well I didn't like looking down that hole. But - to
 get down - there wasn't any water down there you see. No - drinking water of any sort so - in the summertime when it didn't rain at all - well, we were short of water. Really short of water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You really had to ration yourselves did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well we -
 the drinking water was all right but we hadn't got the water to wash with. Do the washing. And of course with all us lot there was a lot of washing. So in the - mother - in the end used to - bung it - that used to get bunged underneath the bed - so the -
 
well, as long as ever it could do, and if it didn't rain - we used to take a - my mother and I used to go with her, if I went by myself I used to take these buckets - two buckets again, and if I went with her we used to have a bath and she had a bucket an
d
 I had a bucket. But we had to clamber over two - two gates to - yes. We had to get over these two gates, and then cross a field - to our pond, and there was only a certain place - in that pond where the water was soft. So by the time we - by the time we 
got home there was - such a lot - probably six weeks washing to do, that wanted a lot - a lot of water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Water is one the things we take for granted isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. We'd got a pond close to us but that was not good for that. Not for doing the washi
ng like that, this was nice soft water and there was only this one place, I remember got - morains and - we always - I don't know if they do now, we used to call 'em mardlins, the green - that green stuff that grows on - grows on - we used - we used to sc
ruff it away like that to get the water out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Like this duckweed and chickweed stuff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes. Mardlins we always used to call it. Quite Essex I think that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your mother or father make any of the family clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 My mother
 made all the clothes. She used to do all the sewing, she used to make all the - the men's shirts, my - uncles and my father's shirts, they - they were blue shirts with - either red or white stripe, very strong stuff. She used to make all that - she used 
to make all our dresses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Whereabouts would she buy the cloth for these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well ever so often you see she - well she had to go and have a shop - a shopping day, she used to buy all these - things. And she used to belong to a - club. What we used to 
call Mutt and Smith, that's a long time ago. Yes, she - she used to go and get all these things and - no, we used to have - we all had dresses, we had to - all had to wait until we had dresses the same and great wide lace all round the neck. All white lac
e all round the neck.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Where would she go, which town would she go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 She - well Southminster. Yes. Although it's ten miles away. That was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did she get there on these shopping days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - she had to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 walk}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  in the ordinary way but af
ter my - aunt got up to the farm so - they had a donkey and cart. And the smaller ones, the two smallest - my younger sister and the youngest one of us, she'd got all boys and my mother'd got all girls, and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  used to go with this donkey. I think that used to walk nearly all the way. It used to walk nearly all the way. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you ever have new clothes or were they always made by your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh, my mother made - always made them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you ever have any secondhand clothes from anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Well very - very rare. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
I mean - if they were they were hand downs from the - another family, which they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Someone you knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. That's all. The only thing that we - we didn't all get them but - but in the summertime when we had six or seve
n weeks holiday we used to go barefoot. That didn't make a bit of difference we'd be barefoot so - one of us had to have a new pair of shoes when we went to school, the others were - they were handed - they were handed down. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would you ever be given secondhand shoes from some other family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. There - there was no - well there was hardly - there was nobody living anywhere near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You were really isolated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We were really isolated. Yes, we were really isolated because although that's 
a seasidey place now it wasn't then. I mean we - the tide used to come up - twice a day, you know how it does, we used to nip across the field, into the water and then out again, we - we never used to bother about anything else. Nobody come to see us.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So that was your main place for recreation was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would your father help your mother with any jobs around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, he did. He -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What sort of things did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well, he'd - help with all the bits and pi
eces and - you know, he'd - see that we got rabbits and things like that for our dinners and - so on and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would he help wash up or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes. Yes. If she was ill or anything like that he would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about in the normal course of events, would he do it odd times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh yes. But - I say, although we were a lot - lot of us - I daresay we were little beggars, he never used to hit us. He never hit us or anything, all he did was lift his hat. We knew at that meant when he lifte
d - lifted his hat, there was going to be - slung at us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 It was like a threat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. He never hit any of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did he ever throw his hat at you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well it's very rare that he did. Anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did he do any repairs or decorating in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well there wasn't much decorating done in the house I'm afraid, not anything like it is, you got your house to live in - and that's a tied cottage, you're not going get to get too much done for you, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you didn't bother much with decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No, we didn't, as long as we got - somewhere where we got - we could live. But I - I do remember when we went there and that was at - Michaelmas - Michaelmas when we moved. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 
And there was a big stable yard - as we got - and as we went round
 there, there was a huge great pile of Victoria plums, they'd picked 'em all and dumped em in that yard, oh there was a - I've never seen nothing - they took all the trouble to dump 'em there.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I wonder why they bothered to pick them all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I don't
 know, they did. All Victoria plums. I mean - well I daresay we could eat some of 'em but I mean after they'd been dumped on the stable yard you couldn't do much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would your father ever do any of the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, he - would sort of - oh sort of general sort of - cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So he was pretty handy around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh yes. I remember - I remember - I don't know which one - sister that was, but I know it was a - a baby of course, and living a long way away there wasn't the - we
ll, the district nurse and things like that, and had an old lady, very old lady, little black bonnet and great big black cape. And was supposed - while she was upstairs we were supposed to be having this rabbit for dinner. My father skinned it and she coo
ked it in a - she cooked it in a whole lump, and by the time it come out for dinner, she - that had got dried up, that was just like - just like metal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Had this woman come in to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, she was an old lady who did do the midwifery those days. 
Yes. Yes. She only just come while the baby was - being - get - getting there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So she'd do the midwifery then she'd also help do the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh she'd probably help, she'd do a bit - little bit of cooking, you know, the meal and things like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So she was a general help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well really old lady - she - well she was a really old lady. I mean, I was young but I mean she was - she was really an old - old lady.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would your father have anything to do with the children very much, would h
e undress you and put you to bed or give you a bath or anything like that when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, we had a - hadn't got a bathroom of course. When we had a bath we were bathed by the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Your dad would give a hand on this would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would he put you to bed or tell you stories or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well we - we'd go up - I don't know whether he told us too many stories. But he - he'd always let himself go at Christmas time, we'd have - prunes and we did get 'em - 
what do they call 'em, snapdragons I think they were. And we'd - he'd always - yes, we always did have those, he always did that, and of course we always had nice stockings. Christmastime we had stockings. They used to - in those days they used to wear - 
long white stockings, underneath their ordinary - under ordinary socks. Great big long white ones like that. We always had one of those but we always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 ied it up at the heel. So that - you know, tied a knot. And we always had a stocking, always had a stocking at Christmas. Where the things come from I don't know but we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Your father would be better off as a farm bailiff than the average farm worker wouldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well he - yes, he'd - yes, but even then you see the money - money wasn't - oh nothin
g near like it is now. I know my - my uncle - used to work there and he - and he used to pay his - sort of board and lodgings out with half sovereign, well that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your father ever take you out at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes. Always at - we always used
 to - at least once a year we - wherever there's a flower show, we always went to a flower show. And we went in a farm wagon - we went in a farm wagon. On the way home we got stopped by the police but we was nearly home and he let us through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was this against the law then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well, yes, we should - I don't think we'd got a light to tell you the truth. No. They wondered what we were doing 'cos that was - you know, fairly late. But I mean, whole crowd of us sleeping on the bottom of it. This wagon.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did the older children used to help the younger ones with things they found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, we all - yes, yes, we had to. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did the younger ones have any jobs to do for the older children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well no, not unless - no they didn't - they didn't too much, no, not for that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you expected to be to bed at a certain time during your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What was bedtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well we always - we had to go to bed early, we weren't up late. Half past seven was the latest. Seven or half past seven was the latest.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh well we - she always used to come and see we was - we were in bed. We used - we used to sleep two - sometimes three in a bed, all depends, they were only little tiny rooms. I know in the summertime that was - mosquito's they were awful. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Mosquitoes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  were terrible. And - we used to tie the ends of the sheet, one end and one the other of the bed, so that they couldn't find us.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You'd sleep right under the sheets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Used to sleep under the sheet, because the - the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 mosquitoes}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  were such a nuisance. And sometimes - I've seen her do that, she's put some - straw or hay - in a bucket and put it in the bedroom, and that'd smoulder and then open all t
he widows and let it - and the old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 mosquitoes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  were out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You didn't have any insecticides or insect }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 repellents}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No, nothing for then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They were real pests were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh real pest, great big things, they weren't none of them little tiny ones, great big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 mosquitoes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What were the sleeping arrangements for the family then, you only had two bedrooms didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, well - in - even in the little cottage there was a long - there's four rooms, one - the end one was the
 - the living room, the kitchen part, and the next one that - I suppose it could be - my uncle used to have that one you see. And then there were the double bed in the next one and the - two beds in - two beds in the - in the room - in the next one.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about at the farmhouse where you just had two bedrooms, where did your uncle sleep then, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I - goodness knows where he slept but he was there somewhere but I don't know where - I don't know where he slept but he was there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How often did you have a bath in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well we - we managed to have a bath about once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - we had clean clothes too, but I say when - we came not with - with water to wash them with they used - to
 be underneath the bed, bunged underneath the bed out of the way 'cos there's so many of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did you get on for bathing in the summertime then if the water ran out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh well we'd the sea. Go in the sea - then. But that didn't do the washing, that would be - wash the dust off. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 While you were at the farmhouse you had two big rooms downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How were they arranged, one was the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 There was the kitchen - the living room, the kitchen, all - oh was a huge roo
m, as big as this again. Well they - they were all big rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did you use the other room for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - I think that was - that was used as a sleep - sleeping quarters. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Your family always had meals in this big room where you cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 In the - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room at all,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. We always ate in the same room.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What sort of cooking facilities did you have there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well a - dirty old buckstove you know, open thing. And iron saucepans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was this a coal stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well, coal if there was coal, we - we did - we used to put wood on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 burn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 mainly wood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Lot of wood we did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What time was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh well, the menfolk - had to go ou
t fairly early, so they - just had their - I don't quite know what they had for their breakfast but they went out and - then they - they used to have a little bit of lunch, my - mother used to make a - well, bottle of tea, hot tea, and toasted cheese and 
we used to - when they were out in the field we used to - if they were somewhere near we used to take it out in the fields and - out in the fields to 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So at breakfast time there'd just be the children and your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Just - I know it was just - bread and jam or something like that, it didn't run to anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you ever have bacon and egg for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh we had - probably had egg 'cos we had plenty of chickens. But - the bacon - I don't think the bacon was very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did you have to drink at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh - yes. Yes, we had tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have plenty of milk on a farm or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, we had to - we had to buy the milk. Yes, and we had to - there was a - another farm - further up where we used to ta
ke the can. And buy it, we used to buy skimmed milk. Well of course it was a lot - also of course it was much - it wasn't half so much money you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about midday when you were at school, did you have a meal at school or did you come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 W
ell there wasn't any - there wasn't any meals at school, those days, and another thing we were too far away - to go, we had to - well it was about four and a half miles to school. We used to walk a mile. And then pick up a - well I suppose it'd be like a 
- funny old cab thing with a little window in the back, you know, and we always - driver out on the box.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was it horse drawn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 horse drawn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 . And we used to - then we used to have to take our own lunch with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What sort of things did you take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh bread and jam, bread and marmalade. Marmalade tart, jam tart. Whatever mother had made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you take anything to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, we just had to have water. There was water - plenty of water there so we just had to have - just had t
o have water. That wasn't too bad, I mean - but when it was - we didn't mind that either, when that was - frosty or anything like that you see the horse - poor horse couldn't get along, we walked all the way. And we were late at - but we were allowed to -
 stand round the fire. To have a warm 'cos we hadn't got in time enough so we used to - warm our pinnies, we used to wear used to wear pinafore, warm our pinnies and put our hands underneath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 It would be pretty cold waiting for this cart to come along in the mornings anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes. I mean that was late. That couldn't get there, that should be there - oh, we used to start out just after seven. Yes. For to get to this place before - four and half miles you see away. Bradwell, Bradwell school we used to go. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So when would you have your main cooked meal of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We'd have that at night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did you used to call that, tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well that was - that - that was our dinner but that - that went for our - more or less for our supp
er and had usually dumplings or - plum duff or - something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What time did you have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well, that would - I don't say it was at - well we used to get back at five o'clock but I don't say we actually had it at - five o'clock so - but about half past five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 And you'd have plenty of things with dumplings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh yes, we had plenty of - well we just had to, you see, you get - fill up with a dumpling and you're soon full up. We always had to sit round a table we had a - there wasn't
 enough room for - we'd got the chairs but there wasn't enough room for everybody to sit so we used to sit three on a - on a stool, and if that one got up that end - that tipped up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 And you had plenty of rabbits did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh was always plenty of rabbits. And we could have chickens and - I mean they were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you used to eat pretty well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh yes, we never went without. We never went without of food. Bake used to come - three times a week. The butcher used to come once. And he'd got a little - sort of like a little - butchers shop one in a box, on - wheels.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 horse drawn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your mother bake any of her own bread at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, no, she didn't bake her bread, well she hadn't got the oven. She had
n't got the oven to do it. She used - she used to make - I know she used to make some beautiful bread puddings and I can't make 'em now. I can't make 'em like she used to. Lovely - and - and milk and - rice puddings. Rice puddings that you could sort of -
 it wasn't dry or anything, you could cut it out in squares and - was what she used to do, cut it out in squares and if we wanted anything to eat during the morning we used to - rice pudding. Beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did she make jam or bottle fruit or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes, she did, she made the jam, of course that didn't last long. She didn't - that - that wouldn't keep you see because - there was too many there to eat it, we had bread and jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about pickles or wines or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well no, she never used to - we weren't - we weren't drinkers or - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 sauce}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  eaters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you didn't brew beer at the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No, the only thing - she used to do - she used to pickle some bullace sometimes. You just put - bullace and put - a little gr
eeny wildy plums, oh I suppose they are wild. And she put the sugar on for so long and pipped them, and then you could have some - they were really beautiful.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You'd have them like a sweet then would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well you could have but we used to - you know, just more or less as a luxury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did she have any homemade medicines or cures at all she used to use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You'd call a doctor in if there was anything wrong would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Well - well luckily - I mean, if it was just a matter of 
toothache sometimes - although my - sister across the way there, she was the only one, she'd have quinzies very badly she really did have quinzies, and we had measles and things like that but - I mean that was just taken as a matter of course.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You wouldn't bother with a doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No. And anyway he was about seven miles anyway. So anything could have happened in that - in that time. 'Cos I know my - we was - out to play, oh there was a huge great field where we used to go and play. And we'd all got 
a - there was my cousins was there and boys as well, we'd all got a - either a tin or something on a stick and making as much noise as we could of course. And this sister of mine, she'd got a - a - was a tongue - glass tongue - like they - they used to ha
ve - they used to have tongue in it, and she put this thing up on a - on a stick. And unfortunately - that came down and that took a great lump out of her - oh that knocked a great big lump out of her - out of her hand. Just gouged a great lump out.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well we had to get a - we - went running in of course and of course - doctor was a long way - long way away. But my mother took one look at it and she went in the fireplace. You know, she couldn't bear the sight - she couldn't bear 
the sight of that. Well I had to get the rags and - do it all up. And although it never, you know, we never had the doctor or anything to it that just grew - she's got a scar but that did grow over. Marvellous how it did. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your mother or father grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes, well the - the fruit trees were there. There wasn't too much attention taken to - if there was any currants or anything like that, well - they were there and we had 'em. We always grew our own potatoes
. Beetroot, cauliflower and green stuffs, all like that we - always grew them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they buy any fruit at all or vegetables?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, very - no, well we'd always the - had got plenty. We always had plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh no, I should - never did see any. No, we never saw any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
How about livestock, you say you used to keep hens and chickens for your own use, was there any other sort of livestock you kept for yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You didn't keep a pig or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, well there were pigs on the farm but that was nothing to do with us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How many times a week would you say you ate meat in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I suppose we'd have our joint on the Saturday. Brisket or something like that, a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 cheaper}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 joint you know. And there was enough sort of left over and that was - made up into a stew with dumplings and - the rest of the week. Occasionally we'd - when the fishman come up with fish we'd have fish. But - they weren't liked all th
at much because they were too boney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 And you say you had rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, we - we had - we'd have rabbits. I mean there was none of this myxie stuff then was there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would you say you ate meat most days or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well most days I think we - we did. Most days we had - we had meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember seeing your mother have less food so the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, I don't think she ever did, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You always had sufficient?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We always had sufficient food, as I say, 
I don't know how she did it really. She - we always had sufficient. As I say we used to be hard up sometime, not much money going around, but we always had plenty to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would your father have more food than anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, I don't think - no, he took his share, his share. There were are.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 If we did we - we soon got called over the coals, no we'd got to be seen and - and not heard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We had to have just what was cooked. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What would your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 parent\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  attitude be if you left something uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - the thing is if you - if there was a second - something to come, you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 couldn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  eat your first you couldn't have any second.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So if you didn't finish up all your potatoes you couldn't have any rice pudding and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That - that was the idea, but we always used to - we used to have - rice pudding 
and custard, we always had that on a Sunday. I know we always had that on Sundays. As a treat I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well we could do but - we'd - if we'd had dumplings or - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Yorkshire}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  pudding or something like that we'd - we used to have a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Yorkshire}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  pudding first with the grav}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 
And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  that give you - good fill up, you didn't want so much afterwards. I like that now. I like it like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 If there was something on the table you wanted, such as the salt, could you just take it or did you have to wait }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 till}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  it was passed to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well we had a - we had to ask for it. Yes. Oh he was very strict like that, he was a real - I say - although he never used to - clobber us at all, but he was very strict that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, not necessary I don't think, I - I think more -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you allowed to bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, we never had any - no, not - not mealtime, we never did have very many boo
ks, we we'd have comics or things like that that we could - we could look at if we wanted to. But - I mean, there wasn't much I mean - even when it was dark in the winter we just - more or less went off to bed. We had one of those little old - Edison Bell
's phonographs and we had one of them but you've got to be quiet with them in case the needle jumped off. That was just rare occasions, that was a treat. Treat for us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh - when everybody else had finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you say grace at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I don't know whether that I - I wouldn't know whether we did or whether we didn't, I wouldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did all the family sit down together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You'd all eat at the same time would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We - we were all round the table. But you see, a stool didn't take up so much room as - three chairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you did all manage to get to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, we did. Yes we did, we all got round the table. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you always have the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Mostly the same places. Yes, we used that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
How was the meal served, would your mother put the stuff from the saucepans onto the plate and just give you the plate or would she put the saucepans on the table and dish it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh no, she didn't put sauc
epans on the table, she used to - dish - well a great big dish - bowl thing she used to have and - if it was stewy stuff and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 She would put it from the saucepan into the bowl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Bowl and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Bring that to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What order were you served in, do you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, just - whatever - whoever - it was just who came first, who was sitting there I think, that's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Where did your younger sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh in a high chair. '
Cos I had a high chair - with a little tray on the front. And that was a little way away from the table you see, so as that didn't - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Who would feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - they - they would get fed in between times you see, a spoonful in and then there's another spoonful in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Who would do this, your mother or you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - mother used to do it usually. 'Cos that's - used to sit up beside her you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 About how old were they before they could sit up at the table and join the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - I don't know, I should think they would be - more or less round about three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What sort of woman would you say she was, was she an affectionate sort of woman, demonstrative or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well just - well I suppose - ordinary sort of woman, she used to lose her temper a bit with us but I mean that was only - natural wasn't it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Oh we coul
d if we got sort of into trouble. I only got - really got frightened once. And that was in the winter time and - we had great big - great big - meat or ditch whatever and that had been - lot of rain and that had come over in the field. And - and of course
 
we all went - off out to play in the field and we were told we weren't to go on this ditch thing. But we did, we went follow my leader behind one and the other you see. And that was - oh that was so slippery and I went down and I cut eye on there. That op
ened it right out there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 This was frozen was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
It was frozen, yes. Well I got up and thought to myself, what am I going to do? So, I just had to keep quiet over that. I just - it just - cut open like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did your mother say when she saw it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well I didn't say anything about it, I was - because she said we weren't to go on there you see. Well we went follow the leader but - and when one fell down the whole lot went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well, just as ordinary children I suppose, we weren't allowed to answer 'em back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You had to show a bit of respect to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. We weren't allowed to answer back or anything. Weren't allowed to say - you know, any nasty sort of words or any
thing like that we weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did they think of swearing themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No. No. If they did swear they swore when we weren't anywhere around, they never - no. No, they never - my mother never - I don't think I ever heard my mother - of course the menfolk, I don't quite know what they do but they - didn't swear otherwise.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh Lord, I don't know whether they thought we - well I suppose they thought we'd still hav
e to follow in their - footsteps, you know. That's where we started in service. We - we all had to - that was a home. We hadn't got one then you see. So it was a home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well they
 always used to - give us - if we did - had got any help - it was - just about may affairs and - things like that and - different odd things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your parents bring you up to behaves towards your brothers and sisters in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well, they
 wouldn't let us - they wouldn't let us - we used to scrap but they wouldn't let us do too much of that even. So we - we just - had sort of to behave. While - while we were at home that was but - I mean, when we all sort of started off out on our own and 
that well of course things went - I mean, that came like - well, I say my mother died you see and there we were stuck with nothing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No. No, we weren't. No, we weren't allowed to butt in. We weren't supposed to be listening.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 If you did something your parents disapproved of what would have happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well, we probably got a smack or clout or something for it. No, we were chastised for it. I mean they would know that we had 
done something we shouldn't have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Who would do this, would this be your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh - no, I say my father never used to hit us. No, he never used to hit us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So discipline was in your mother's hands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 In mother's hands. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did she ever use a stick or strap or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No. No, she - she never had a stick but I remember - and I think it was only my - sister - who's over there - there again we were all out and we were round pond - and - we were thr
owing bits and pieces in, bits of wood, stick and - stones and things like that. And the sister - below me - threw herself in. Oh - she threw herself in, that sister over there she - slithered down, of course she'd - petticoats galore which hung-hung - he
l
d her up a bit. She slithered over the edge and - and - got bold of her, just said, well we got her out and - during the commotion - my father and mother come out you see and I think he did catch her - on the end of her little finger with a - a strap or s
omething he did. But that was all. And we had to go - up to bed and no tea. All of us. But we did get some 'cos I mean she crept up with some after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So your mother would be a bit soft hearted afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes. In she went - she threw herself in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would your mother often send you up to bed, was this a usual punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That's the usual - that was the usual - that was the usual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That was more usual than a slap was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 But you say she'd sometimes relent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well 
she'd give us the food. But I mean when we'd gone upstairs to bed at night we'd gone upstairs, there was no hanky panky up there then, you'd got to go to bed. And was up to sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember how you felt about being punished, did you used to resent it or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well - we - I suppose - I - I can't remember but - only once when I know when we - we hadn't - had much rain and there was just a little rain and we put - baths and everything else out to catch as it came along. We tipped the thing ups
ide down and hit the bottom - hit the bottom of the bath with a stick. Oh and we did get into trouble. But into trouble then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What happened on that occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh dear me, dear me, we did get a - a slap that time. But I mean we - we deserved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you'd get a slap when you were actually doing damage more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes, but there - there was - it wasn't - it was a slap, you know, nothing sort of too hard, they just made you feel it, but it was nothing to - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 vicious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  or anything about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, much about the same. Yes. I mean then when we - we started - when we started out to work of course - 
we got - well - we lived in big houses. We - we lived in really big houses, we lived above our station, we - we did. I mean, we had to work for it but we did live above our station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What do you mean by that exactly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - I mean - we were - cla
ssed then as the - and these people was - like a little higher up with a bit more money. And that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So what do you mean you lived above your station, you had better food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We had better - better food and we - better - different people, higher up people. Very - you'd got to behave and do -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you feel that domestic service....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Wonderful - really. Yes, really. That was really good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You feel it opened your eyes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes. Oh yes, yes, that did I mean a - thing's got 
to bed one just - that you see. Not slap-dash. At least it wasn't where I went and I only had that one place. There
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you feel that was quite a good training?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, that was a - that was a really good - that was a really good training. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 That\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 what I say, we've had - we've had good training and one thing and another, now - as I say, now we've got older - well - they just say we know too much but it isn't a case of knowing too much, it's just knowing how to do it. You see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 When you were a child at home would birthdays be any different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, not necessarily, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you get cards or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No, there was no cards or anything. We'd probably have a - little bit extra cake, you know, over a Sunday or som
ething like - mother used to always make all the cakes and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would you receive any birthday presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Very rare. I can't remember ever - ever receiving - anything. No, not as birthday presents. Mother would say, well birthday, oh it's a bi
rthday, you buy something. That was just a birthday and you were just that much whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You knew it was your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, you knew it was - they knew it was your birthday you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would you have a party, would you have any boys or girls in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No, there weren't - I tell you there was no people about near us. There was no other people there to ask. The only time we used to have a nice little treat sometimes when my mother had got a - a sister and - she'd got boys. She'd got all boys
. And he was a skipper on a barge. And - well I don't know how they - they just sort of - they used to tell each other if they were coming, they used to pack all the stuff in the bottom of a - funny old pram which - was as hard as hard. Flour and bread an
d jam and - marg or whatever, it was marg that they brought. And they used to come, there was a whole houseful then, we'd have a quite a little party - of it. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How long would they come for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well they'd only - they'd like come on a Saturday a
nd go back on the Sunday, and they used to walk a long way too. Right down there and they used to come from Upper Hawthorn. That's a long way. But they used to walk along with all the kids. I suppose my mother's sister. And - I think }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 he\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  still alive and I'd like very much like to see her, I think she lives at Chelmsford somewhere with her - with her daughter
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You were telling me about Christmas Day earlier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh we had crackers. We always had crackers. Yes. We always had crackers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Can you tel
l me anything else that you remember about Christmas Day, did you do any activities with your mother and father, or did you have any games or this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, we was much about - I say we only just had - mostly it was in the evening we used to
 - we had a candle - we had - we used to light the candle, and then have these - prunes. And - we'd get 'em - then they were lit up you see and we had a hot mouth of these -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Cover them with brandy and set fire to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, but I don't think it 
was brandy, it was a bit of whisky, we did have a little whisky then. And once we had a - we had our stockings and - they were all dropped on the floor. And they weren't hung up anywhere, they were always dropped on the - each one - at the bottom of the b
ed where each one - each one slept.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would you have any presents at Christmas, you say you'd have some nuts and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, we had - we always had nuts. Nuts, dates and figs. But we always used to have them done up in a little paper in our sto
cking. Always had an orange in the foot. Orange at the end, and then we used - nuts, dates - and figs, and - we always had a new penny. How they managed to get the new pennies but I don't know but they did. We always had a new penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would you have any sort of toy as well or not?
