\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Amongst the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes, we always sort of played -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would your mother or father join in with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 My uncle used to play mostly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Your uncle probably taught you did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
We used - we used to play these - dominoes mostly we did. They weren't quick enough to pick up cards or anything. Anyway - that was more or less a gambling thing so - we didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Your parents didn't agree with gambling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No, they never did anything - anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have a newspaper in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 YES, we had newspaper. I think there was only one on a Friday and there was the Essex Weekly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You didn't have a daily newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, there was no - no, nobody came. No, we was right out in the wilds you see, nobody ever came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you just had this weekly paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We just had this one weekly Essex paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, there wasn't - there was nothing - had no - there wasn't the money to pay for all those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember your mother or father reading at all, were they readers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - my father couldn't read. He - he - he just couldn't read. And my mother used to read the paper inside out to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 She'd read aloud would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. He - he couldn't read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember any funerals in the family before 1918, you'd have both your parents wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Could you tell us anything about those, the clothes you had to wear and who came and things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well the - the - my - my father - he was, I say he was thirty-six, my mother was forty-two and that's six years afterwards you see. Well I don't know too much about the - father's side. But I know he was terribly ill and they brought him }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 downstairs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 - got him downstairs in a - a whicker armchair. And they took him - they took him to Maldon Infirmary or somewhere at Maldon, of course he never did come back - anymore. So that was the first one, and we had the funeral there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they bring him home from Maldon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
They brought him there and - and the - church - that - is at Steeple. I don't know if you know Steeple, and that's right the - the church is not there but the church yard of course is still there, that's like stuck
 in the middle of a field. That's where - go down to Maylandsea Bay or somewhere along there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have to wear black or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - we did then, but I mean it weren't sort of too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have a black dress or just a black band or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Had a black band mostly. You know, for outside. My mother wore black of course. Huge great - huge great - hat. Huge great - great big black hat she had. And - long frock down to the ground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about your mother's funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well, I say I'd been up to Hutton - oh, about a couple of months when they - sent for me. And - where the lady was rather dubious to whether I should go home although it said come at once. She - she said, well if that's anything infect
ious like fever - I said, well I wouldn't think it's going to be fever, not there. Oh my goodness, that was dark on - you go to short cut and I - I walked where I could, I ploughed across some fields and over a farm gate and all the rest of it. Seven mile
s and I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How far did you get the train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Southminster. Yes, and walk the remainder. But I knew there was a short cut there through this thing and I didn't know whether there was any cows or anything in the field but I - got there and walked along
. But I was too late. She wasn't there. Well I say, she was there but - she wasn't there what I could see of her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Who came to your mother's funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well that was a just a sort of - ordinary sort of poor affair really. Of course there was my old
er sister, they'd sent - sent for her and she'd - somebody was supposed to have gone out and meet her and pick me up as well but - we got lost in between somehow. A different odd time. And my - and my - this one aunt that - she'd come all the way from Haw
thorn and then she - she'd walked that way and then she'd walked all the way back, I don't know how she did it 'cos she was getting on. She was wonderful woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your aunts and uncles come to the funeral or was there just the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 There w
as only - was only us, the - now - just us - few. And she was the last one who - she was put in this - churchyard affair, next to him, and she was the last one who was put in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was your uncle still living at home at this time, was he still lodging with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well - he - of course he had to move out somewhere - afterwards, there was nobody - he did keep a little - cottage on for a little while because - he was - missed everybody. And in the end he - he got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 He did marry and have his own home eventually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
He did. He got married and had his own home. After - he's dead now of course but he did - but he was - you know, he used to help us with - eventually as we got a bit bigger eventually we had bikes and he used to fork out for 
bicycles, you know. Oh yes, he was a good - he was a good help, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relatives at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No. We never visit - well there was nobody there much. Only sometimes, when we got a bit bi
gger - we used to just go and see my grandma, but I mean that was just a pop in and a pop out, but she always made us welcome.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How far away did your grandmother live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh - five or six miles it must be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you couldn't pop in too easily could you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. But - she - they'd all ways make us welcome. And always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Who did you used to go with, your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, usually with two - the two - the - sort of children more or less. So we'd go on a bicycle you see, we had a bicycle each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you ever taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well - when my mother used to go - when - when she went to have a shopping day - at Southminster we used to - go and see the shop but we could just look and that's about all. I know we always had a 
- we always had one of those ice mice. Pink and white iced mice. At Christmas we always had one of those. The -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Are these the sort of things they used to put on a card?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, they're sweet. They're sweets. They were pink - made with icing sugar I 
suppose. For mice, pink and white with a little tail at the end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you ever go out with just your father, or was it usually a family thing with your mother as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well, we walked out - we walked out all as a family. You know, but usually acr
oss fields 'cos - I mean, you couldn't go anything - any - anywhere else much. We just sort of - he's probably looking all around, seeing how things were going on. And - horses were out on the marshes and he used to just look and see if they were all righ
t and - things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you'd go for a walk just for pleasure more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We - just for pleasure, yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember any other outings with your parents, you say you'd go once a year to a flower show?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 To the flower show, they were nice then. They were very nice flower shows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would that be Southminster again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - mostly it was, that wasn't too far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you ever go anywhere on Bank Holidays or did you have any holidays at all when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You never went away at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Never - never - never had a holiday. As a matter of fact I haven't had - myself, I haven't had a holiday - oh, since about 1923. I haven't been away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You haven't been much of a one for holiday making?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No, I'm not much of a - only - the only holidays I've had is when I've been - had a fortnight in hospitals. That's only holidays I've had. And that still doesn't worry me, you know, I - I like being at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Could you tell me how you spent your Saturdays in those days when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well - got all sorts of mischief I suppose. You had - you - used to have casks - you could get casks you know, beer casks. And - round tins, there was a big - great big field and - we used to get on the to
p like they do on the telly, only they use a ball the telly, well we had a - couple of sticks that - used to get on top and walk. Stilts we had. We used to make our own amusements. You just had to. Yes - we just had to make our own amuse - amusements.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have things like shuttlecocks or footballs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
We had a little tennis ball occasionally, but that - you know, to play with but - I - I don't know once or twice we seemed to get an old racquet from somewhere, but - I mean, they didn't seem to hang on. You know, they didn't seem to appeal.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 It was mainly making your own fun?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes, making your own - making your own, yes. I know we used to - we used to get round the - when I was - was quite small and we used to get round a - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 cart shed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 , in the cart shed and - jam pots and the tin and a bit of something we used to scrape all in between the bricks, you know, all the - we used to make lemonade and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 ginger beer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  and - oh it seems awful doesn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You'd play shops and this sort of thing would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes we did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You used your own imagination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes. We used to scrape all the red - dust out you see, or white or whatever it was into these - pots and things and then put water on it and stir it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That used to colour it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would you drink it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, we never - we never used - we never used to drink it, no, we never - we never did that but - that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That made a stock for your shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes that did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well Sundays was always Sunday school. We had to walk quite a way to get to that even. We used to go across the fields again. You know, short - short cuts. And - that was a - Methodist chapel, little Methodist chapel. I think that wa
s at Lower Hawthorn. There was an upper and Lower and that was at - but - every Sunday we had to go. And I remember I had a - as we was going home, I don't know whether it was a car or what it was that came along but I know I - I had a - astrakhan - littl
e round astrakhan }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 hat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 with a - brush stuck up at the side. And I'd got this - the coat as well I think went with it and I - took the - lost the button, the button came off me coat and I put in it me mouth and somebody grabbed hold of me quickly to go across
 the road and I swallowed the thing. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How often did you used to go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh nearly every Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would this be in the afternoon or morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. That's in the afternoon. Yes, we used to - we used to go to Sunday schoo
l in the afternoon after - that was dinner time you see. YES? WE went in the after - always went in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have special clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, yes, we had - the Sunday, but they was all taken off when we got home again. And put on one side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you allowed to play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, we could - we could play around but weren't allowed to make too much noise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You'd have to be a little bit qui}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 ter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Quieter, you know, so that you'd know it was Sunday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your parents think it wrong to work on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh no. I mean they just had to you see. Yes. Yes, they just had to work, there was no - getting out of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They - this - this Methodist - chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They'd go along with you would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We used - they used to go along up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How often would your parents go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I don't know how often, quite how often they went, I didn't take particular notice 
of what they - of those times, but I know we - we - went every Sunday afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would both your mother and father go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes, they - yes. Yes. Yes. He didn't go so often of course 'cos he couldn't get away. Got too many things and that to - y
ou know, on a - on the farm to see to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh yes, we had a - there was usually a - a park or somewhere. You know, we used to have a - at Christmas time we always had - they always had a party up there as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Where was that held?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well that was held in the - I believe that was held in - in the chapel I think. In a huge - they had a huge tree, Christmas tree. With dolls and everything else on it, I had a doll - a lovely little doll but it was - a wax 
face. And - and of course that was put away on one side and - and - mice eat it. The mice - ate the candle you see. And my sister had a - I suppose you'd call it a magic lantern, you know, you turned it round like that. And we all had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you'd get a present from there at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. We all had a little present at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Which park was the outing too then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I haven't - couldn't tell you now quite what the - where it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How would you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well that wasn't - it
 wasn't - that wasn't the - the park for Christmastime because that'd be in the middle of the - you know - because you couldn't - you couldn't do much in the - in the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What would this outing consist of, what sort of things would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well in the summertime it was - races and things. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Children\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  to - usually }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 things. But I know when we went to school we - we used to go in the - it was the Bradwell - believe it was Cann and Owen then but - we used to go in there, but - the one thing th
ey used to - we always used to have our tea and all the cake and that was cut up and then - you know, plain cakes, fruit cakes and - seed cakes and I didn't like that, now - all seed cake underneath the seats I think we finished with. And they used to - t
hey used to have a lot of stone ginger beer, you know, in stone bottle, and oh I didn't like that, oh I couldn't bear that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Who was this given by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I suppose really that would have been given by the church school or something like that. Or so
mebody - I don't know who found it all. There was tea and that, we used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you ever go to the church or just the chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We - well we - when we lived - at - the other way we used to go to the Methodist chapel. And - but when we got to S
t Lawrence Bay there wasn't a chapel so we - we used to go - St Lawrence church. Up on a - that was right up on a hill. There wasn't very many people got there but we used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was that Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That was church of England, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your parents used to go that as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, well I mean - I say I don't mind whether it goes Church of England or what it is. Providing you go somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 This was your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 parent\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  attitude was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. YES. Yes, Sunday was Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were there any other social activities organized by the church at all that you used to go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You had the Christmas party and the summer outing, were there any clubs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, there was no clubs or anything. There - there was always 
that business of - so - isolated you see, there was always that business of getting some - someone to get you there. I mean - they - well I suppose there wasn't the motor cars then, where they could come and fetch you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 It was this problem of everyone living so far from everyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes. That's what it is, I mean, you'd got for - you'd for miles and wouldn't even see anybody. But what I always thought was nice about the country was - we weren't out very often at night when it was dark, but if yo
u were on a bicycle and we suddenly come along there, they'd all say goodnight to you, even if you don't know who they are. They don't mean anything but you know it's very friendly. That's friendly to think that there's somebody around. I mean, they'd be 
foreign round here - if you were to say that, speak to somebody - round this way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you belong to the choir or anything like that at the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No, we just used to just go ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you know whether the church or chapel ran a temperance club at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I don't - I've got a faint recollection of something like that, but I - I don't know too much - not too much about the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Fireside prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you ever have family prayers or just say them at your bedside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Just ordinary - just ordinary, you know, round the - round the bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your father take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh, not much I don't think. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I think h
e was a Liberal man, but - I - he never used to discuss things like that with us. I suppose he thought girls didn't want to know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What makes you think he was a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I always know when it came round to elections he'd always got a yellow rosette. So I know he - he - he was a Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your mother take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, not - no, not to that extent. I suppose she'd do the same he, if he was Liberal she'd follow - follow up with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember your father or mother voting in a general election at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No I can't really. Although they - they must have done, but I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You just remember him having the yellow rosette?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. He'd got a yellow rosette. I can - I believe the - the fellow's name was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Butler}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 {\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 or some such name as that. You know, they made a little parody about 'em and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 In some places at that time men felt that they risked losing their job if they didn't vote the same as their employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well, yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you know if your father felt any of this sort of pressure at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
I don't - I don't think he did, I - I think if he - whatever way he wanted to vote, he - I mean he wouldn't - say what he vote, you hadn't got to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you don't think he was under this sort of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, no, he wasn't under this - he wasn't under any pressure like that,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember if your father did any work for the party at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No he didn't. No, not for - I can't remember anything 
like - no, he never - he never used to go out at night either. No. He never went out anywhere at night, only time I - my uncle used to go out was when he'd got to go and pay his - club somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How would your parents spend their free time then when they weren't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well, just walking about or - you know - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 usually}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  in the garden and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Doing their garden mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your mother have any interests outside the home, were there any Women's Institutes or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. There was nothing, there was nothing. No. Nothing - nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Not by herself, she never went out by herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Her only outings would be the flower show?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, yes. But I
 don't think she minded. I mean - yes, yes, yes, but I mean if you live in the country you live in the country and you have to - you have to do - that's a lot better now but I mean you have to - go as the - country people do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How many evenings a week would your father spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well most of 'em I should imagine. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would he ever go out to a club or a pub or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 He never used to drink a lot, we'd - sometimes if we had a walk out on a Sunday, he'd have - we'd all w
alk round. He might - they might call in at a little pub up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So he wasn't a strict teetotaller?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh no, he's not; no, no. We all - we always used to have garibaldi biscuits. But weren't allowed in of course but we always had garibaldi biscuits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would your mother go in the pub with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well, no, she didn't hardly - ever went, she'd sit outside. No, we weren't pub - we're not pubites. We never were pubites.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your father take part in any sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No. There wa
s nothing that he could - well I say, whether he did that even I mean before the flower show there might be a tug-of-war, he might have a go at that, but I don't - I'm not so certain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would he attend any races or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Nothing there, no races or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Weren't there any points to points or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would he have a bet at all on anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs, any clothing clubs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well, my mo
ther used to belong to a club because I mean that's how she used to get - you know, she used to pay so much and that's how she used to get - the - clothes, some of the clothes and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How was this organized, was this from a shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Y
es. That was organised from a - you know, you - probably you - well you'd put on what you like, if you can afford a shilling or two shillings you put two shillings on. And at the end they probably give you two shillings - you know, on the pound or somethi
ng like that. I didn't believe in things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about burial clubs or any sort of insurance, did they do anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - I think - of course there was a lot of us and my - think - well my mother was - thought on that li
ne I suppose 'cos I mean she didn't know what was going to happen. And she always - she put us all in for - it was only a - penny a week }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Prudential}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 . Well a penny a week, if there was six or seven you see that's going to mean - in them days it meant quite a
 lot wouldn't it be. Well - we all kept this - penny a week thing, and I don't know how many times I didn't say, oh well, I'm not going to have it, I'll give it - 'cos when I married I had - took it myself you see. I said, oh it's not worth having at all,
 
penny a week, I said. If I can pay a month of a whole year I said, I'll - I'll still belong to it. That's what I did, I paid once a year. And then I - had a word with my sister 'cos she'd got one and she'd been in it - by being a bit older she was in a bi
t
 longer than I was, and - I said, oh I'm going to see if I can't give this up, I said. I've made arrangements should anything happen to me, I said, I don't suppose that'll all that much out, I said, I'm just about fed up with that thing. So I - after all 
t
hose years, I - I don't quite know - I was quite young. And after all those years there was only about fourteen pounds to come out. So I just - well that - yes, that would - that would have been a lot, but I said, oh that wouldn't even buy one side. And m
y husband was the same, he didn't believe in insurances because he said they don't help those who want help. So he - he -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did you get on with your sisters, you say you didn't have many other people to play with, was there anyone you felt particula
rly close to as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No, we were - you know, we all sort of - messed in together, mucked in together. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were there any other children close enough for you to play with or was it just the family you had to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well the - there was my cousins. They - they live at - they were boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How far away did they live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well only about - like up the top of the farm, when we lived in the farm you see. When we moved down to this other little - bungalow thing and - they moved into the farm so it was just - about the same distance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So did your uncle take over the farm bailiff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 He - yes, he took over that job you see. 'Cos that had to have a man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Had they lived near you before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They used to live next
 door to us. Now - no, I've just remembered that - that was called Marsh Farm, Mayland. That's where we moved from. And we used to live next door to that. And that was the same man -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So the two families would move round together would they more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well - he followed us when we - had to come out you see, he - took that job on. His my aunt and my father was brother and sister I suppose that's how it was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you had your cousins to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 YES? but I say they were - they were bo
ys. There was no other children - there was no other children anywhere around. Yes, that's just - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Whereabouts did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 In a field. We had a big - we had a big field.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What sort of games did you play, you say you used to go swimming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
We used - oh yes, we went - across the field for - for a swim. But I say we - sometimes - we got a - we had tennis balls and we had some racquets from somewhere. How we got those racquets I don't know, but we - we never played -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you used to do much mushrooming and blackberrying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, we did. In that field where we used to play. We used to go out and my - mother - used to make the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 ketchup}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 . And they - it was a seaside place, there wasn't many - houses or anything but there was - seve
ral people who had, you know, little cottages that they used to come for the summer. When they went back she used to make pints and pints and she couldn't get enough bottles to put it in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about rabbits, did your father have a gun or did he used to snare them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
He had a gun, he had a single and a double barrel. And that was always - stuck up in the corner of the kitchen, but he always unloaded because - we were girls, he unloaded it you see, in case anything happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did he used to do any wild fowling, did he used to get any ducks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, he didn't do that but they used to go - catching }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 els.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They used to do a bit of fishing did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They used to - yes - no, that weren't fish. Well - eels are fish, you know what I mean, but 
eels. And it was caught with a little sort of a long fork with a prong, I've seen it sometimes in the Reverend Wright's - what do you call it - the countryside, on a long pole and they used to have a punt and they used to dig in the mud like that and it u
sed to - they used to get -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Is this what they used to call a shear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Eel shear, yes. Yes. They used bring 'em home, my - my eldest sister used to - well she would have to skin 'em you see don't you. She used stick 'em in a bit of wood like that wi
th a fork and then cut it all round, skin off. No, I - no - I don't like snakes and I'm afraid eels make me think of snakes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about things like moorhens eggs, did you eat those at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, we didn't - never ate them because they're rather strong. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 
Or seagull's - but we did have - peewits' eggs. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Used to get quite a lot. They used to make their little - nests just - oh, no there wasn't a nest, just stuck on the ground you know. We used to have those, they were all right. About the - I suppose about as big as a pigeon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Were there any other sort of things, did you used to have elderflower wine or anything like this, anything else you'd get from the countryside more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Mostly there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 plenty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  of rhubarb so we made rhubarb - rhubarb.
 Elderberry wine - used to - you know, it was too much trouble. There was too much trouble attached to it but - rhubarb, I've made some rhubarb - matter of fact I made some rhubarb wine for the dustman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Could you tell me more about your father's job as a farm bailiff, what size of farm were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh I'm not much good with acres but I know it stretched a long way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So it would be at least several fields?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh - yes, that - that went round a long way and that went out on the marshes, some o
f the horses were put out on the marshes. And there - you know, they had a great big - I suppose you'd call it a dyke. Very wide, where these horses used to get their drink. And of course when it got dried up these things'd - go in - as far as they could 
a
nd then get stick in the mud. So - well we used to have to take two horses as a rule and a - great lump of rope and a - a wagon. So that we could - sling the rope round the horses neck and pull it out like that. If that wanted a ride home well that got a 
ride home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So your father would need several staff to work on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Oh yes there was several people that worked on the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 And he had charge of these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 He had charge of them whole lot of them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Any idea how many men he had working for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh I don't - I wouldn't - I wouldn't know how many - actually how many he'd got. Because - I mean - for one thing, we were - all girls, and he was one of those who kept the girls out the way of all the animals and things like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Where did these staff come from, you say there were no other children nearby to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - well, they were grown ups, you know, young men. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They weren't married with families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well some of them were, yes, they - but the
y used to cycle - cycle to work in the morning and thought nothing of it. They just came where the work was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you didn't have farm cottages near you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 There - there was a certain amount of farm cottage, what they called tied cottages. Yes,
 there was a - there was a certain amount - of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
How did your father get on then, you say he couldn't read, how did he get on with paying out wages and accounting and checking the corn in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I - well that I don't know but he was pretty h
ot on these, yes, he - he couldn't read. He couldn't read but he was - he was pretty hot on money I mean he wouldn't get cheating for anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So he'd know his figures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes he did. Ye he did, he knew his figures. But I mean that - that wasn'
t too much. You know I - I had an uncle, the same uncle that - took over the farm house when we left. Well he took that over as - like manager of it, and he'd got a son who was a horseman. Well the son wasn't very old but he got a lot more than what the -
 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 ploughman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  did. Yes he did. Because he was a horseman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 He got more than the bailiff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes, yes, he did, he got more than the father did because he was a horseman, he had to get up four o'clock you see and so on. Yes, that was - I mean that was rea
lly very poor money. I mean - I don't think somehow that was about twenty-seven shilling thirty shillings or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Who was it your father worked for, you say he always worked for the same chap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, he was a - a man named of Haydock. He was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 He must have been a big landowner then was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
He - he'd got a big place at Purley. Yes. He was always a man name of Haydock, he used to - got these farms you see and when they - when they changed over they went onto the other ones.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You say your mother didn't bake bread and you didn't have an oven for bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh no, we didn't have a big oven. But that was just an ordinary, you know, with the bars across it. I think - the oven about that size. And then the bar and it was al
l - it was all open on top. One of the really old fashioned ones. Oh no, she never used to do the bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you ever eat tinned meat at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh no, we never thought - thought about having tinned meat. Then we always had plenty - plenty of meat 
of course - although we - we were - you can say poor if you like but we always had plenty of food. We always had plenty of food. Enough to fill us anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 After your father died you were talking about your mother's jobs and your mother dying, you say 
she had been helping out at a boarding house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did your mother manage after your father died, what did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well she - she used to - go out seasonable, always used to go out in the field. Trailing we used to call it I think. Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 es}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 ? trailing. And - thistle dodging you know before that was really cut }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 down and}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  then she used to go and help this lady - they used to have boarders in there and - she used to go and help this lady with the - well the cleaning. I mean the pay was very bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would this be all the year or the summer only?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh that was only the summer. That's only the summer you know 'cos with visitors. 'Cos I used to go with her when - when I - I should think I was about seven. And I used to go with her and - oh she wa
s a - oh she was a big lady you know, a huge great lady. And she sent me upstairs to do the dormitory. Up the little tiny narrow stairs. And I - went up and - did what there was to do up there and - and got myself down again, and when I - got down, she sa
i
d - she just twittered me, and - went over the top of me and she said, did you - did you remember to - take the cobwebs down? I said, no, I hadn't. And to this day I always remember she said, you know you must always - bit religious lady, she said, you mu
s
t always remember to look up. And for a long time, as soon as I went into - it was very embarrassing too, when I went in somebody's house I'd look up to the ceiling - for cobwebs. Yes, but I always remember that lady - that - that - great big lady. Great 
big - well I suppose you'd call her a boarding house lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You were talking about the games you used to play as a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you ever conscious of being lonely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, when I got - the first - the first job I had when I went a
way there was little children there you see and that was quite - that was quite nice. I know they used to; they - I had long hair, very long hair. And when I went up to dress and that for the afternoon they used to love combing my hair out. You know, comb
 it all down the back but that - that was quite nice sometimes too to have it combed out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I was thinking of while you were still a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I wasn't very old then you see. I wasn't very old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I wondered if you felt, after having been at school all week, that perhaps Saturday with no one else around except your family .....?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No - we used to make our own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You never noticed the lack of other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No, we - no we didn't. No. No, we never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - that didn't crop up because there wasn't anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would your mother and father let you play with any children do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I think there was only my - cousins who were there that we could - that
 we could really play with, we couldn't - there - s mean, it was down the lane and probably the next house hadn't got any children or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have any hobbies at that time, did you collect anything or have any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. We - we never thought about keeping rabbits or anything like that. I mean a lot of children had rabbits but we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have a big of garden of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh we had a little - yes - round the back of this - little - cottage thing where we used to live - we had
 a little bit of garden about that wide. All allotted off and we each had our own little bit that we could grow a few flowers, we used to call the - they was beautiful too, we used to call - it primrose cottage and it used to look lovely in the summer.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How birds nesting and things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh we used to go bird nesting. Yes, of course we went bird nesting, used to - but - I mean, we went bird nesting but we never took any. We didn't take any because I mean there was no sense in taking them. We
'd just like to find them. To see how many there was. And then we'd keep going back to them and see - when the little ones were there and - so on, when they'd flown off. Oh they were really happy days. I mean, to what the children are now, all they think 
- is destruction now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You say you used to go off swimming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well - we couldn't actually swim 'cos we was only - little, but I mean, we used to - we used to stay where we could touch the bottom. We used to get covered up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You said there was no one to see you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have swimming costumes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No we didn't, no, we just - just used to take our clothes off and hop in. I - I know - I remember very well my - my mother and my aunt, she came to the - they came with us
 one afternoon and they sat on the beach and they suddenly thought they'd like to have a dip. Well - they couldn't go in with nothing on of course. And how it came about like that I wouldn't know but - in those days my mother used to wear coms. So she too
k the coms - off and sew the two legs up and - they went in and had a dip and - both of 'em, one had to put wet ones on of course. Yes. Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 es}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 ? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 They}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 - they was the wet - one was - there wasn't - there was no need to want costumes. There was nobody ever to see us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about if your cousins were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh - well we never used to - they never used to bother - they used - they were a little further away - until they got in the water you see. And once they were in they were in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They'd just go in a little further along would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes. Yes. And there was all the cliffs where you could - you could undress and - on the cliffs, there was nobody - nobody could see you. But then that got stopped you see during the war days. Well - there was - there wa
s all barbed wire and - well they had a - they thought they was - it was like a backwater, and they thought there might be an invasion so they - oh - well - all put - all barbed wire up. And then they built a - the - oh I don't know what the thing was I'm
 sure but anyway it was manned by the Royal Marines. And - they had to do duty on this thing - a big thing - and whenever the tide was up you see we - steeplechases - used to come along and - do their patrol.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You say your uncle bought you and your sister a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes. That was a made up one, that didn't - some of the parts didn't fit but - the wheels went round. They weren't very - they weren't very much, I don't know, I suppose about five pounds or something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember your oldest sister being at home, she must have been about ten years older than you mustn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 My eldest sister, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 She would have left home fairly early would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh - oh yes, she - she - I mean, I wasn't very old but - I don't 
- well I doubt very much whether she's alive now 'cos my - sister round there is seventy-four, so - that would bring her up somewhere - but she wasn't - she - she wasn't a particularly healthy girls, she used to have - weeping eczema all over her hands. W
e had an awful business with her to - you know - keep - couldn't - with so many of us we couldn't use her towels and things like that. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did she manage to go out to work then or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, in the end she did, she went to service at - Rochford I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you ever go to the cinema or concerts or the theatre all when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
The only - thing - no theatres, and no cinemas. Not there. And the only way we could have a concert we - where we went to the concert was - the people who were on holiday, they used to have a little get together. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Pierrots}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  they called them I think. And they used to make their own little concert.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was this at St Lawrence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, and we used to have chairs - and sit out. You know, on the lawn. They
 used to have their long verandah where they did their - where they did their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 periods}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 and - stuff. There was one poor man, I don't quite know where he came - he came from up London somewhere, but he'd got a - he'd got a terrible carbuncle on his bottom, an
d he'd got to play a duet. Oh dear, oh dear. It was a thing they - they quoted you know, there was a whole lot of them, a thing that they - he said, I went to a country fair and who do you think was there. You know. And that all got muddled up in the end 
of course - the monkey sat on an elephant's trunk and so on. But we used to like those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So it was becoming a little bit of a holiday resort even then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 YES. There was - there wasn't very many. But there was this one big boarding house. And then - 
I don't suppose there was about a dozen - and they used to let 'em out you see, one have a holiday and then another one - he'd come - yes, and one man bought a railway carriage and he - he had it like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have any pocket money while you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, ha'penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was that regularly every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Regular every week. We had a - we had a ha'penny every Monday morning. And we - always had when we went to school, because I was only little then, we went to school and - we had this
 ha'penny every Monday morning. And we had to have a handkerchief because we had handkerchief drill at school. We used to have this ha'penny - pinned onto our frock, tight in knot in a corner of our handkerchief. Then we'd go off during the dinner time an
d
 - spend this ha'penny. And there was some beautiful - what they called - ice stuff. Coconut ice, that's right. And he was a very old man, he just lived on his own - beard all round and he used to smoke shag, that place smelt awful really. But we used to 
just go and say, can we have a ha'porth out of the tin please Tom. He'd put on a paper and go off and eat it, that was the cheapest that we could get. But that was beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did he make it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I don't know how he - I don't know how he got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did he have a sweet shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No, it was only just this one little room, and he used to have this - coconut ice in a biscuit tin. There was no measurements or anything he just give you what he thought. We used to say, give us a nice lot for our money Tom. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh now. We had - whatever there was we - well we were girls and we all had to help you see, do what we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did you get on if your mother was ill or confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - well she was ill of course but luckily she wasn't - ill enough that she hadn't - you know, she could always superintend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about when your younger sisters were born, how did the family manage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - this
 - we had the midwife. And she used to do - part of the cooking, I don't quite know how long she came for, about a fortnight or something like that. And then my father used to get the - you know, the teas and things. And my oldest sister. Yes. My eldest s
ister used to - well we take - we had to look after each other. We - we just had to look after each other.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You had one auntie and your cousins living near you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 And your grandparents lived fairly near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, fairly near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have any other relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well you know what a village is, the - one marries one, one marries another and then you're all sort of inter - you've got - mixed up like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you see much of your relatives at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, not - all that - much, but we did recognize 'em as - relatives. You know, when they're just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 passing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  by I think well there's nobody, but we did recognize 'em as relatives. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 Sometimes}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  we used to go and - stay with - I'd got two grandmas then. We used to go and stay with her and I - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 was a peculiar little house but we never took particular notice of it, I know it was up some stairs. And when you stepped on one end of the board that used to tip up the other side and - and old - and the old bath used to dance up an
d down and - and I shall always remember we - when we went to bed I'd got a chaff pillow. The chaff stuck through - oh it was awful. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was that your father's mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, it was my mother's mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Where did they live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Wel
l - it's - I think it's called Marsh Farm, or Maylandsea Bay now. There used to be a little - a road that turns off, and this was only a - well an old wooden place - but there again you see that belonged to the - the farm and they didn't sort of particula
rly care. I don't know where ever the water came from. I think it must have been rain water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 This was when you lived at Maylandsea was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We used to go - we used to go and see her after we got to - St Lawrence Bay, yes, we used to go and see. Ye
s. I say they were - when you - look back on 'em they were really lovely days, you know, we used to thoroughly enjoy ourselves. We really did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were this family of cousins who lived by you in St Lawrence living near you in Maylandsea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They used 
to live - Marsh Farm Mayland that was called. Mayland, there's a Mayland - and a Maylandsea Bay, they've got boats and that there, you go to sort of another part. Yes, they lived next door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So the two families must have been quite good friends, they deliberately moved together did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well they were - they was brother and sister you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 If one moved the other would as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Well not - not necessarily they didn't necessarily move that way but - that's how it happened.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your parents have any friends apart from their relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I wouldn't say they were - sort of friends, but they acknowledged everybody. You know, they weren't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would there be anyone come round and visit your house or would they go and visit anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well only just a short call. Yes, it - was awful business to get anywhere. We - - if you went anywhere - you had to just walk - and that took a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 If friends called in would they be offered anything to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh if was g
oing to have tea they had tea. It was - I - as I say, probably there wasn't too much but we always made enough for all of 'em when they had tea. We used to have one of those - which was most peculiar too - we used to have one of those little paraffin lamp
s
 that stood on a little tiny leg, and that was in the middle of the table, how it never got knocked over I don't know. I really don't know how that didn't get knocked over. It was one of those that had got a very - little narrow chimney you know, with a g
l
obe on it. But I think about the worst - the worst part of it was - the toilet. I mean - that was all of a half mile up the garden somewhere. Weren't they? I expect the - round Todmorden and Purley all round there you would find some like that. Even now. 
B
ut I - I think the - they've improved on those because they have had Elsans and things like that. But we didn't, it was just a - just a matter of a hole and it's - emptied so often you know. We - when we went like for - in the wintertime we used to have a
 
- what being a lot of us there used to be a - hurricane lamp, we used to have a hurricane lamp, we used to have to go off round a corner. But when one went the whole lot had to go you see so there wasn't open and shutting the doors and letting cold - and 
there was a - there was a - a - a big and a little seat for the babies you see. Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 es}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
. Oh yes. Yes, was just the ordinary - just the ordinary seat, you know, just ordinary wooden seat and then this other little one at the side for the children. In fact there 
was - there was one down here when we first - down this way when we first went there. And that's how I moved my chickens up to here. I'd got chickens, I had a lot of - lot of chickens and I thought to myself, how ever am I going to move them, 'cos they ma
d
e such a commotion. And I waited 'til that was a bit dark and I'd got an old pram belonging to my daughter. I said, don't throw it away because that might come handy, I can push four wheels better than I can - do a wheelbarrow. I thought to myself, oh wel
l I'll - I'll wait 'til it' fairly dark and I'll put this seat with the hole over the top of the pram and put the chickens all in there with a sack over the top, and that's how I got 'em up here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 People often tell us that in those days people made their own amusements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did your parents do when they got together with their friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well they more or less used to - you know, just have a chin-wag. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 
Just - you know, the events, all what they've done - yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I 
mean - they didn't - well they didn't gamble mostly, there wasn't any cards, there was only - the younger ones who go into a - gambling state. But not - my relations, they never - gambled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Many people divide society into different social classes, at t
hat time before 1918 did you think of some people as belonging to one group and some to another, were you conscious of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You don't mean in your own family do you? In the other circles, yes there was. I mean, there was you who had to do the work. 
And there was the next ones - little highest up who paid you to do it. You know they all seemed where you had to say - yes sir, no sire, three bags full sir or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What would you call the class you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well we'd - more or less the working class, we were the - we're working class, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What would you call this higher group who used to pay you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I don't know if we would call them really anything but they were the ones who'd got the money you know and they we
re - oh - I say where you just got to say yes ma'am, no ma'am, all things like that. They expected you to do that you see and then they - if they thought they were a little bit better than you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you conscious at that time of a class below you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
I don't think - I don't think there could have been any, there - no, I think - when it got down to - down to our level they were all near enough the same. Certainly there - there was some you know who - well you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 could}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  - just could not help. Who you - you - they wouldn't let you help them. But no more if you - you hobnob with them just the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What sort of people would you say belonged to the same group as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well they all - they were all workers. Yes, they - they couldn't do anything
 else, they - sort of - all worked on the farm. There was no - factories or anything. Very few shops, but they didn't want those. No, they were all farm people more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you weren't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 conscious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  of two different groups within the working class at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well - not what I call the working class on the - our level, but the ones who were a little bit - you know, a little bit higher up, they did think - well - I don't know
 what they think when they came for a holiday but - I mean, they were the ones who thought they were a little bit - better off than we were. We were just country bumpkins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You feel also it was a bit that they were townies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They were - yes, they were townies, that's right, that's just what it was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember any distinction between craftsmen and labourers in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - there was the man who knew his job. There was a man who thought he knew his job, but he weren't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid208827\charrsid15539754 much}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  
better you see. And they - and there again, if it was something that - I mean, the boss probably would come along and said we want this done today and we want that today and we want something else, and - you just do it. I mean you - you so used to being t
old what to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you think some families were thought of as rough and others respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes. Oh - very much so. A rough - a real - a real rough family, they lived rough anyhow. It - it's rather difficult to describe but they did - they did, t
hey really lived - you know, really rough - sleep out and - although they'd got - some of 'em had got homes to go to they just slept out. Yes. They were really - really rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you mean scroungers and cadgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Cadgers, and they weren't clean. They didn't bother. Well matter of fact I had an aunt like that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Funnily}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 enough her mother was Aunt Liz, and as we went to school in this thing the driver used to - just look through this little window at the back, he used to say, here comes Aunt Liz. She'
d go along so fast and her skirts - swept along the road and - you know, kicked up an awful dust. And she'd got - well she had, she'd got several children and they were all named out of the Bible. Every one of 'em. And they got on as - they're doctors and
 
- everything else, they really got on really very well. Well I should have said they'd have been a bit on a - scruffier side and - although she used to have things given - clothes and that. If that didn't fit the one that she thought she'd put another lit
tle bit on the bottom and that -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 It was just done anyhow sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They had a house to live in did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, they had a house to live in. She used to go blackberrying. You know, in the summertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did her husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh he worked on a farm. You know, they was all farms, there was nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 She just didn't seem to manage very well, was that it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, she didn't, that wouldn't matter what you gave her. I mean, she - we used to say, well it's no 
good giving it to her because she'll only - cut it up and then that'll look no good at all. As I say her family really - got on. Ever so well, got - some of 'em went to Australia and got on - you know, up ever so high.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No. I mean these people used to come in - for holiday time, we used to think they were a little bit better. We used to collect their milk for them at - there was no milkman brought you 
see, no milk brought to the door. So we used to take all these cans, oh ever so many of them. Some'd want a quart, some'd want a pint, some'd want three pints and they began to get a bit heavy. And when we got 'em we used to - we used to charge a ha'penny
 a pint for whatever it was that - for carrying them, getting them, and that's how we used to have our bit of pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you used to look forward to the visitors coming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 The visitors coming, that's just how, we used - you know, keep count of what we got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you ever told to curtsey or show respect in these sort of ways to anyone?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh if we went to a - if we was a - you know, proper Sunday school anywhere and we just had to go up to take a prize, we were - we had to - curtsey really you know, and - we were all dressed up, we always - did - used to wear pinafores.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What about this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 chap}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  your father worked for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh he was quite a - well now, he'd be one what I would call in with - some of the gentry. And he was a working man too, he worked. See.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 He was a working fellow too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, he was a working farmer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would you be expected to curtsey to him if you saw him in the road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well you wouldn't be expected to curtsey but you'd - you know, show a bit of respect for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would the men touch their cap or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, oh yes, that always went up like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So it would be the men rather than the women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Mostly, yes. And the women - didn't get the jobs like they do today. I mean, they used t
o go and - pick potatoes, something they - just when they were - well, ready to be harvested and that. They didn't get very much money for that even.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was there anyone you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Not really, because we didn't - we didn't k
now too many. We didn't know too many people, there was only the - you know, the - like this Mr Haydock who - paid the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in those sort of ways, should anyone touch their cap to your father or
 anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well - I think a good many people did, I mean, if they were the poor as they used to touch their caps. You know - had just a bit of respect. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Because your father was the bailiff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 And he could employ them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 If they went for a job. And there was one there going, but they could always do with some in summer. Plenty.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 In your village or district who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 The parson mostly. The - he was - he was mostly - the
 one that there was. And there - there was a - another farmer where we used to get the milk, they thought they were a little bit better. But they had to work just like anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Who do you think the clergy mixed with in their spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well goodness knows, 'cos there was nobody for them even. They used to live in a vicarage it's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How about farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I mean - well the farmers, well - they had a farmers meeting. They did. I mean, that was nothing to do with anything much, they 
were - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Which class would you put the schoolteachers in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Schoolteachers? -Well I - I don't quite know - I don't know quite where the teachers - came from. 'Cos I mean we used to - we could changes of course. We always had a - up to - oh a lot
 of years, that was a big school and that was partitioned off, one for the very little ones and then the next ones, and then there was a classroom for - oh - standard ones to twos or something, then the boys. Was the other end. Woe betide us if we found w
e'd got the door - you know, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 peeping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 through the door. But at Christmas time we all had sort of - bit of carol singing. They used to - be - Canon Owen and - some of his relations, they all used to come. And we used to have a bath bun. We always had buns at 
Christmas. Used to bring 'em in a basket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were schoolteachers considered important then or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
We had a - we had a governess. We had a governess for a long time. And then I don't quite know - how it come to be - 'cos they though I suppose we - 
we ought to have a - schoolmaster, so we had a - I don't know whether you heard anything of him but his name was Romwell and he used to live at Tollesbury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - there wasn't many - really m
uch - they - if you hadn't got anything to get there with you'd got to walk and they weren't going to - turn out, and I remember we went one - they used to keep maids at the vicarage of course. And this man, he was a huge great man you know, got a big - a
 
moustache and he used to go and see his daughter in the afternoon, she was a housemaid I think, used to go and see her in the afternoon and they used to go to church and - they sat behind us and there was a tune that he didn't know. And he just - said in 
a loud voice, isn't it a damned funny tune? Yes, he did. Mr Fenner his name was. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was he another farm worker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I don't quite know - I think he - I think he worked on a farm but he lived - Bradwell somewhere. But he - he used to come and see h
is daughter you see, because she was the housemaid. Maybe he stayed to tea, I don't know. Then he'd got to walk back again. Of course that was quite a way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you notice any difference in the congregation of the chapel from the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What sort of difference would there be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
There was more free and easy. They let theirself go. You know, and they really put all their heart and soul - into this - singing. And we had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 Peculiar's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  chapel. I don't know if you've heard one of them
. Yes, there was a Peculiar chapel. This - I say this aunt that I was speaking about - she used to go to there. But they - they did - they used to let theirself go more than the - Methodist. I mean they used to say yes and no and if they didn't believe it
 in the middle they - they'd say so wouldn't they. Yes. Yes. I remember - whatever there was you'd find it and I - we used to wait outside and hear them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 
Get the door open and they say - amen to this or something like that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 YES? yes they did. And that was a
t Steeple. The Peculiars chapel. A lot of people haven't heard of them you see, but - of course they'd have to be - well, getting on if they did - know anything about this sort of thing. They wouldn't know what you was talking about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different social groups or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
I don't think it's much - distinction. No. They used to respect the boss or his wife or something like that. You know - or the parson whoever but - there was no sort of bowing and scraping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
What about the local shopkeepers in Southminster, what sort of class would you put them into, would they be working class or the upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - no, they'd be the - they'd be the working class. There - we used sometimes we'
d go to Steeple, that was only three miles. But that was a very little small village. A really little tiny village, you couldn't get everything there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How would you think of those shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well as just shopkeepers. You know, somebody who sup
ply you with a little food and give us our stuff that we wanted. No, they weren't - no, not as - no, not anything above you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to any particular social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I don't think she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You don't think she'd be conscious of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. I mean she - she had to work, go out to work like anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was it possible at that time to move from one social class to another do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I don't think they did that, they stopped, you know, they stopped with their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 More or less what you were born to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Well - what they were born to. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 There were mighty few of them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8084273\charrsid15539754 There were very, very few of them.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What would you call that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
I mean you wouldn't think they - they'd probably come and - think they were ladies but I mean afterwards you'd say oh I don't think much of her as a lady. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You think it would be more a matter of behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 As a - yes, just a matter of behaviour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - occasionally we did and if we did we knew there was something wrong. They were out to catch somebody. 'Cos we use
d to have a sea wall - we used to have a sea wall, that went round the seawall from Maldon, all the way around to the seawall and went round there. And - I know we - Saturday afternoon there was a funny little man, he'd got a - red cloak and all - gold br
a
id all round it and all these pots and pans - hung with a - he'd got a tall hat and of course - anybody we saw like that they were tramps. But he said that he was working - walking round the - world by the seawalls. But we all ran of course, we just said 
he's a tramp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were there many tramps and travellers in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes had a lot of tramps, don't see no tramps now. There was a lot of tramps then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you see more gypsies in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 es}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
. Yes, we used to - have an old gipsy - lady, I don't know whether gypsies are all G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
psy Lee's, but she - this one was - this one's name was Witney. But they'd got - oh they had got a - beautiful caravan. The brass shone on it. Oh it was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you frightened of the gypsies when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - we didn't think too much of 'em. But I mean we weren't - taught to be afraid. No. Wasn't much good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your father employ the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 gypsies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  at all for the casual work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No, they were - what I should call respectable sort of
 people. You might - little further afield 'cos I say we were a little bit off the beaten track. And if there was a farm - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 gypsies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  would get - you know on a pea field. And they were really rough then. They had an old tent and things like that. Quite often - they were just as good as us I suppose but they were still gypsies. Tramps some of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You were frightened of tramps were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, we didn't like tramps. No. We'd run a mile for a tramp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your mother ever threaten you by saying I'll call a policeman or frighten you with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, she - they never - no, she never used to frighten us like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How do you think the policeman treated people in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Very lenient. I mean, he'd very often turn a - blind eye. Somebody wit
h no light, on a bike. No. There was the occasional ones who - who - well really got - they were doing a bit of - stealing or something like that. There was the occasional ones who got - oh no, he'd go well into it first. And it'd be - more like if he did
 it'd be more like the - well a little bit of the upper class who put him onto 'em you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you think he was more or less on the workers side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, he was. Yes. I mean he shut his eyes to a lot of things. But he lived quite a long way away,
 I don't know whether ever he did patrol.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you pay any rent at these farm houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No. No because they were tied - what they called tied cottages. That went with the farm, so that - if you left the farm, you - well you usually followed up into another one where there was one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did you feel about your landlord, the chap your father worked for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well I mean, we didn't always say that - he was a landlord, really, I mean - dad used to work for them and - that was just that. If we had to move we had to move you know, we weren't - interested in them enough really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you remember while you were still a child feeling that your family had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh, very often they did. They did have a struggle, but I say we always had plenty to eat. There was always a struggle to make ends meet.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you conscious of this while you were still at school, or is this something you realised afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - we hadn't - we didn't know anything else, I mean, when 
we were younger and going to school, before we went to school, we didn't know anything - really know anything else, so that when we started off and earned our own money - we just - we didn't make too much - there wasn't - there wasn't the distinction made
. You know, 'cos - we were earning our own money and - so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you ever get any help from the parish or from the Guardians or any sort of charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That was called - when my father died of course - and there was a whole lot of us we got a princely sum of five bob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you ever need any while your father was alive, was he ever ill or anything for a period of time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, he was only ill that - he was only ill - ill and that took him off you see. He got perforated ulcer at the end and that
 just took him off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So your mother needed help from the parish after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh well, she did try, I mean to say, she tried but there was nothing much - occasionally we'd get a pair of those thick sole shoes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 From the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 From the p
arish. And - I say she got the princely sum of five shillings. And I - I'm not absolutely sure but I believe that this - was paid by the parson. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 It would be the parson she would have to see to get this money would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Be the parson, because
 that'd be the parish. The five bob - you know, the things weren't all that amount of money those days, you could buy quite a lot, couldn't you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 It isn't much though is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. We used to have a - used to have our groceries, groceries used to come once a fortnight. So we had bulk - bulk }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 sugar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
. I don't know how she did it, she used to - get by - buy bulk sugar and - I don't think we had too much butter of course, that was - we had bread and jam, I like bread and jam even now, I don't like butter on me bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How do you think the parson treated your mother, did they come and see how much furniture you had or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh no, they didn't bother about the furniture, they didn't bother about furniture. But he'd got a fairly - big 
garden and when there was - apples or anything like that he always used to send a - basket round. But some of 'em weren't all good mind you, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you think he treated you pretty well or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, I think he did, he always used to come and
 visit. I mean the - although he - that was a long way away and I suppose nobody would tell 'em but - when my father was - yet I remember 'em quite well the - this big fat lady that was telling you - towered up above me, she came up and - there - there we
 were, the whole lot of us, kneeling round the bed while she offered up prayers. That was the only way we could at it really you see, we couldn't get to the parson anywhere. He was very good like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 When there was someone in the district whom people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, I don't think so, they - there was people that they didn't like of course but they - they never made }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 an}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  issue up out of it. No. They - they didn't like them but - do
n't know. They - they just - well they just carried on, they didn't - make any difference - do it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you given any lessons by one of your parents or anyone before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - we used to - one - one or two, we used to have our tables and - little sums that went down like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 This was before you went to school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. That were - I mean, we get along up to about three or four or something like that. We had to - well - when one been to - they foll
owed up 'cos they weren't all the same age you see. Oh we all had schools. We played schools, that's - what we did, you know, in the ordinary way. One'd got to be the teacher of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So your oldest sister would teach you this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 She - she'd be the - she'd be the teacher. There was usually a little bit of a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 scuffle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  who's going to be teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh when I first - oh - that one, I - when I first went to school I was about three and a half. And that's when I lived - we lived at L}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
tchington. We lived - we lived down Marsh Farm, but that was still Latchington there. I was only three and a half when I went to school. And we had to - we had to walk a - oh, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 quite}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  a long way. We had to walk a long wa
y, and there was my - my two eldest sisters and - cousin that was a little bit older than me. And at that time they had huge great - tam o'shanters with a bit of wire - they stuck out all the way around like that. I know - you wouldn't remember them I don
't suppose. Well that - they went then of course they were very difficult to hold when that - if that was windy. But there was two big ones and two smaller one you see. So we used to - if that was snowy or too windy, we used to - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 screw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  the wire up like that and make it smaller and get - the two smaller ones got inside the hat but - the two - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 bigger}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  ones led us - led 'em along. Yes. And that was at Latchington, that school is still there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You wouldn't have been at that school for long though would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No, we were - I wasn't there long. Then the next time we went - there was a little - school at St Lawrence, but - there wasn't enough children there to - want a teacher, and that was a lovely little school. That wasn't used, no. So we had to have 
this horse drawn thing, you see, to get us to Bradwell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well we'll talk about the Bradwell school then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What was that - elementary school I think it was called.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What time did you say you had to leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh - quarter past seven at the latest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What time did you get back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 About five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So it was a long day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That's a long day. We used to take our lunches with us. And I mean to say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What kind of school was it, was it a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, I think it was - I think it was - connected with the church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 The boys and girls were in separate classrooms were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes. There was - one long - one long - piece, there was a piece went along the bottom - one long bit. This one end was for the real - little babies
. You know, little tiny babies. - And then the next - the next bigger ones - was for the bigger girls but there was a classroom leading off and a - well I suppose one to eights or something like that. And the other side of that - 'cos - the little boys we
re - in the - the - what we called the infants, the little boys were in there. But they didn't come in the other room. The boys were always boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you miss many days schooling during the winter and this sort of thing? It must have been difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well it was a bit difficult, but I don't think we - we never used to all much. I mean, unless - we didn't miss - many days unless of course it was - some sort of - something like measles or something. But we never had days off you know to go out on a j
aunt or pea pick or something like that. No. Because they used to say, no, you - you can have your holiday, you - you - you'll have to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did many children take time off for pea picking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, a lot of 'em did you see, that's just it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 But your parents wouldn't let you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No, we just - maybe we were a little bit too much nuisance at home. But there's one thing about that school, they would - they used to - I think it was called the Kings Head - Kings Head in Bradwell High Street and - th
ey used to have a meet, you know, hunt and hounds. And if there was - a meet there, the school - the whole school went out to see 'em. Yes, that was quite nice. I mean, some of 'em played a bit truant and got carried away and went off. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did you think of school, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I didn't - I didn't mind it - I didn't mind it at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well we had one teacher we didn't care a lot about, and she - she was the governess. And she
 used to have a little cane of course. Not that she used it all that much to you, that was - usually on our hands. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 
But there - there was one of the bigger ones she broke canes up so she had a little hedge stick about that long. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Little stick she cut out of the hedge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They broke them up when she wasn't there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes, they used to - they used to get a - well some of 'em who - I suppose they thought they'd got a little bit - too big and they used to grab 'em out of her hand and - yes and break them lik
e that. And I know - know - Miss - Miss Jaycock her name was, I don't quite know where she came from but she - that was her name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So children just refused to take the cane sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, they - yes they did. Yes, they really refused to take the
 cane. They used to sort of stand up to her. You see, and take the cane away from her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would this be boys or the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, the girls. Well the boys had the canes 'cos I mean - they had the master the other side and that used to come down there and whack.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, you said something about taking your handkerchief for handkerchief drill, what was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We had handkerchief drill, yes, every Monday. We had to have handkerchief, well -
 we had our drill out in the playground. Well, whether that was - not if it was snowy, but we always had our drill, first thing in the morning, you know, up and down and that keep fit thing. And we always had a handkerchief drill, there we'd all got to bl
ow our noses before we went in, there wasn't any sniffing afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You all had to blow your noses before you went to your classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, we did. I mean that wouldn't matter if that was a bit of rag with a - just a - you just had to have handkerchief drill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they teach you manners or emphasise anything like this or tidiness or cleanliness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh well, of course they - oh I suppose what all the schools - more or less should do. That's one thing what they - don't call it grammar now but 
they used to teach us grammar. I think they call it English at the moment, but they used to teach us grammar and we had to do lessons on grammar. And we used to do copywriting. I don't think they do copywriting now. It's all print - now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they emphasise ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Oh yes. If there was any that - you know, were a little bit - backward they did try with 'em to - get them -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they try and make you talk B.B.C. English?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh no, - it was - well like the country you see. It wa
s like the country that they'd been used to. I mean - that's almost like it is round here. Well if you get into Suffolk and get into Brightlingsea, it's up and down thing, it's so sing-song. Isn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 If you did something the teachers disapproved of 
what would happen, you say you got the cane if it was something serious, what other sort of punishments were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well we - stood up in a corner. We stood up - in a corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would they give you lines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, we had lines - yes, we had lines. Oh yes we had lines. During a - during the playtime where we should have been out you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They couldn't keep you late because of your bus could they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We had to - get home, they couldn't keep us to get home. Otherwise we'd got to walk all that way and there'd be trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well - they couldn't go and visit, you know, they didn't - have really what you call open days like they do now, just see how your children are getting on. The
y couldn't, they was too far away. And they never even though of - well - providing the transport to - you know, to get you there. But they used to do some beautiful needlework, my sister used to do some lovely - beautiful needlework, we always used to - 
but then we - we used to have a show. Show it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 The school had a show?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 school'd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  have a show and show it. Oh some - my sister used to do some beautiful stuff, she - well she's a good needlewoman now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your parents ever meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well unless there was anything special - there - as I say, if you got enough }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 attendances}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  and there was a - lot of forms and everything else to fill in then. But they - normally they - they wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did - the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes, all of 'em. You know - sort of country -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I don't really think they did. No, I - I don't think they did, I mean - we might have thought probably there was favourites but -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No, nothing like what you - nothing compared with today. Oh no. Oh no, we couldn't have a set-to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were there any children left out of things do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No I don't think there was any - anything - it come - when it come to the time of the - 'course we had our dinner, we had a - to stay to dinner of course. When it come to dinnertime it didn't take us all that long time to eat
 our meal. When it come to - spinning tops we used to take our top for spinning. Spin it up and down the road, sometimes that'd go over the vicar's wall and sometimes it went over - sometimes that went over in the churchyard. Oh used to have - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you go to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, that was the last one that I went to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - I - I wasn't fourteen. About thirteen and a half - I'd just got enough stamps - stamps I was going to say, but -
 I'd just got enough }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 attendances}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 . I mean they had to go back for several years, see that I'd made enough }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 attendances}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 . And whether they thought they had to have a teachers committee, whether they thought that - I could go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would you have stayed any longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I should probably have stayed 'til I was fourteen. Or something like that. But I'd got this little - I'd got this little job -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would you have liked to have stayed longer or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I don't think - e
verybody - every child - think they want to leave school, but they don't bother so much when they got to it you see. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you take any part time education after school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, I - I just learnt what I could and that's - and I went along as I went along.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 While you were still at school did you have any part time job or any means of earning a little money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 N
o. No. No, we didn't earn - couldn't earn any money, there was nothing - well - I say - we didn't get it, I mean even when we worked in the fields I mean, we didn't get the money, the money went else where. Yes. That went elsewhere, to buy something.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I - I went away and looked after these three children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You went away to service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did you get this job, how did you know about this job in Walthamstow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well a sister of mine was a maid in a - farmhouse at - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 Mundon}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 , I think they called it Mundon. And this sister of hers was the one that had got the three children. So I - I went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What exactly did you do in this job, you looked after the three children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well, yes, and 
- and I had to look after the three children and I - just did ordinary other you know - helped the usual sort of little things and that. Then I got a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That was housework was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well there was just a little but nothing much, and I got a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 princely}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  sum of one and six. Yes I did, one and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What sort of hours did you have to work for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - there was nothing - really - set time. I mean, I more or less lived with them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have any time off on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I
 didn't want time off really, I'd got nowhere to go. I used to take the children out for a walk or something like that, I - up by - Epping Forest. And there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you were more or less almost one of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes. Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 es,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  no set hours. No, tha
t wasn't - well there again they weren't - well all those people who were really well off. You know what I mean, they weren't - some of those that you'd got to say - yes ma'am, no ma'am sort of thing. They were - they were - they were like ourselves - mor
e or less like ourself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did the man of the house do at that place, what was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well he was a milkman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 A milk roundsman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Milk - he - that was his own - his own business - business, but he was a milkman he used to go and
 get the milk, milk churns they were then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So he was a working man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes, yes he was. I mean they hadn't got the - the money to that extent to - not to pay you any sort of wage - I don't think any of the wages are very high. Very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well that wasn't a fair wage but it was - that was start wasn't it. I used to live with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you give any of that money to your mother or was that all pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh I couldn't, that was a - just - that was only just my own. That was all I could do with my own money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did you get on with the people at that place? How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh - quite well. And they were quite nice but - as I say more or less like ourselves you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you like the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, I liked the - being with the kids. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you think this job altered your attitude to school in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well it was nice 'cos I didn't have to go to school of course. That was after going to school tha
t was a - you now, a - ease up wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How long did you stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
I wasn't very - I can't say the exact - time, but I wasn't there - long, because I - as I said, I - wanted a bit more money and they - couldn't give it me. So I went where I could - and I forget what I got there, five shillings I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were there any other servants there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. Not there. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Just yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 From there you went on to Hutton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Hutton Mount. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You worked there quite a number of years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes I did, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 That was 1924 wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Married from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did you hear about that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well it was during the war days and we had - soldiers - Royal Marines I think - and this lady was his - moth
er-in-law. And she wanted somebody and - so I - just went there. That was a three storeyed, three storeyed house, you know, quite big to - what the other one had been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did you do in this new place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I did the housework and there was a l
ot of work in there. There was a lot of work in there until - November. When I - had the other - next sister to me - she came so she did a little bit of housework as well you see, we were both there. We were both there together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you didn't have children to look after there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, there was no children there. But there was a lot of - they entertained quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What sort of hours did you work at that place, were they set hours there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh that was six to any time. That was six in the m
orning any amount, was any time, it all depends what they'd got in. I mean she always - we had half a day off then. But we had to be in by nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have any time off Sundays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We used to have one Sunday - afternoon off. Yes, we used to have
 one Sunday afternoon off. One was in and one was out. And - but I mean - usually on the - usually that was the after - the other one - afternoon off in the weekday, she'd suddenly think she'd like to have some people to dinner so there was - probably - s
everal people to dinner and there was three course dinner, you'd got to cook it and dish it up and wait at your table - as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you get any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, we had - we had a week. No, I think we had a fortnight's holiday there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What were you paid at this place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh about five bob, it wasn't much. I mean, -we were paid - end of month, by the month that was paid, by the month. But she never used to give us our money when it come to the month, we - always had to ask for it a
nd then by that time we want to go and do some shopping and that was all gone. I suppose she thought we didn't want any money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you feel this five bob was a fair wage or not at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well that wasn't a fair wage but that's all you got. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 Ye
s, that's all it was, it was - well they used to keep you, you see, so I suppose they think your food and - your bed and everything, that was - all included in it.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were there any other servants at this place apart from your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 When you first went there you were on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I was on me own, yes. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh well, she had her moments of course but otherwise she was - she was really - very good, she - we used to help of course, we used
 to - cut the grass and one thing and another when we could. And she'd take us up to London for - day's outing. Yes. Oh we went to see Chu Chin Chow, I remember that as easy as winking. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So she'd take you out sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, she used to take us out for the day and - we used to go and have a meal out you see. She used to take us out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did she used to address you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well just by your - just by your name, our Christian name, not a - not a - another one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did you address her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well ma'am, madam or something like that. You just - you just had to. Or I mean otherwise you was called over the coals you was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you feel that she was interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, I think she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 because}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  I think she thought -
 we were on our own and she was showing a little interest, she - she would always sort of get worried if she thought that - I mean, if she heard a car come up and she thought one - one of us was out she'd wonder how we got there, she was soon out on the -
 in the kitchen to find out - who'd brought you home and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you think she'd give you a bit of moral guidance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, she - yes, she would, she would, yes, oh yes, she was like that. I mean sometimes she was quite all right, I mean - I kno
w we had snakes and ladders, she'd come and sit in the kitchen and play snakes and - snakes and ladders with us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So it was quite a friendly atmosphere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes. But if there was sort of - anyone there or anything like that you'd got to be 
in your place, I mean you couldn't - you - you couldn't just sort of go - well - sort of mix up with them. But during the war days I mean, the war - nights come to that when there was air }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 
raids}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  and that we all used to - mix up together. The whole lot of us and - and there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  no li}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 ght}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  - we couldn't have any lights, we had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 of - well I always used to call 'em stinkers. They still are stinkers to me, them little tiny light like that you know, with the little tiny - little tiny wick. A little night light thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you think it was the air raids and things that made you more friendly or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes. YES. I wasn't - there wasn't - shelters - I mean they were zeppelins those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you homesick when you first went away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I'm afraid I couldn't really say I wasn't but that's not much good was it. You have to get over it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You were the only servant until your sister came, did you feel lonely or did you have enough company?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well there was plenty of people around. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 There wa
s - all - plenty of people around you know, they'd always - talk to you and - their - their visitors come and they get to know you, you see.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Is there anything you particularly liked or disliked about working at this place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No, not - no, not
 particularly. The only thing I thought sometimes she was mean. I often say, oh well she isn't half mean, I mean there's a quarter of a pound of tea got to last for so long. But I mean during the war - if there's an air raid there was - tea for the mornin
g, tea for - tea for something else and then we'd got to have a cup of tea at night when that was all over. And she used - just used to say that - well he did, he always used to say that - girls have used rather a lot of tea - tea this week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So she used to supervise things pretty closely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes she did. But I don't think that did any harm. That didn't do any - that didn't do any harm at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, I used to do washing. Well except the - his collars and shirts. I didn't do then. They were sent to the laundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Who made or mended the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well I don't know whether ever I saw her mending any, but - she used to make a lot of her own clothes. She was a - and sometimes she used to keep herself very poor because she was a matron in a - in a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 hospital at Hackney. And if - well they were bad girls and things like that, if they hadn't got any clothes or anything to go out with she used to - cut her own up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So the master and mistress were both working while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh - yes. Yes. He was a brick manufacturer. Of course during war days - that wasn't there, but he used to run a farm then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Who did the cooking, did she ever do any of the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well sometimes she did, but I'd rather do the cooking myself because - she made more mess
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So if she cooked you'd still have to clean up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 And there were no children at this place?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well they had a grown up daughter. There was just one grown up daughter there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was she out at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. She didn't do any - she didn't do any work, she - when we used to go work in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 field}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  in the land army she used to come out with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You joined the land army while you were there then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - I suppose you'd call - it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 auxiliary}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  really. But that was recognised you know. Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes, 'cos that was a green - don't know if you remember them, green armlet with a - red crown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 But you still stayed and did your domestic work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes. Oh I - we still didn't - occasionally - if there was something on - one would go and the other one - take it in - turns, one'd go in the morning, one would go in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you get extra money for doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, they used to give us a - I mean, that come out of his pocket, that didn't come out of the - that come out of his pocket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Where did the family eat their meals, what sort of domestic arrangements were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh well we - we ate in the kitchen of course. But 
our plates on a table - on their table - in the dining room. Our plates went on there and that was served out and dished out from there. They'd dish up the meal, we used to have the same, practically the same as what they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What sort of cooking equipment did they have, did they have gas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, I don't think they'd got a gas oven, it was ordinary kitchener. Blessed old black kitchen oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What time was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well he - usually managed to go out by nine so we had breakfast and
 that in between that. He had - porridge, we had oatmeal. Sometime we had - if we got syrup we had syrup or treacle. Otherwise we had salt. Oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they have a cooked breakfast, bacon and egg?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, they had - yes, they had bacon and egg. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have the same as them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes, we had - we had - we had the same. We had the same as - what they did. That was all put on the - all that went to their table. And then our plates went with it. And - when it was dished out we just had 
to - go in and fetch it. And I know the - latterly I mean they - she wasn't well and they had a - had a - cottage at Great Holland. She used to come down here, she used to bring one girl with her and leave me behind with him. And - well that wasn't - we h
a
d to have just what we could in the way of meat. And this - of course they were a little - you know, in the know and there was this ox tail came along. This oxtail and I'd never - I don't know what it was, I - I wasn't - couldn't have been about fifteen I
 
shouldn't think, and I'd never had an oxtail in my life, I'd never seen one. Well I - I tried it - and - dished it up you know, at night. And when I went I could have laughed. When I went in he'd got it in his hands picking up the thing. Yes, honestly he 
had. He said, I think that wants a little more cooking. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What would they have for lunch normally, would that be a cooked meal or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well that was a - was a - more or less a makeshift - mal. I mean - she used to do some funny things
, I mean she used to bake paste with split peas and a little oxo and - little bit of marg on top you know. That was paste. As I say, she was so tight but I don't think that did any harm. Really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You'd have your main meal in the evening would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. We'd have our main meal in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What time would you have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
That - that was usually about half past six. Well that took us all the - evening then to - clear up and do the washing up, not much time after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What sort of meal would that be, would they have soup first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh yes, they always had soup first. They didn't have a plate then, one of those little round things, you know, with two little handles on the side. Oh a three course dinner they had, and if there was an
y special - body special, then they always - more. I mean, they seemed silly little bits, little tiny bit - a bit of bread and on it and a bit of cheese on top. Oh - I mean that'd all got to be got ready and if you were only one that was a bit of a - do. 
And we hadn't got a hatch, that was the only thing about it, there wasn't hatch in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they have any special food on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We had a joint. We just had the joint and - Yorkshire pudding and - you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Pretty much as usual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Y
es, but I think sometimes they - they cut the soup out on a Sunday 'cos I suppose they thought they'd have - Yorkshire pudding and - we had some afters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they do any bread making?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Or jam or bottled fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh well she used t
o do jam, and - bottling. Oh yes, she did and I know she - during the day she - well there was a lot of people ill over that, too, a lot of people boiled rhubarb leaves. Yes, they - they did, they boiled - they boiled rhubarb leaves and - what did they ca
ll it - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 botulism}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 . They }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 poisoned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  theirself you see. But the funny part, we cooked them, they ate 'em and - my sister and myself, we never had any and they couldn't make out why we were all right and they - and they were all - so bad. Yes, rhubarb -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 This was a wartime idea was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. YES. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 Boiled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  rhubarb, oh no, I don't - I'm not going to - I - we didn't fancy that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they grow any of their own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, well they - they used to keep a gardener. They had a gardener. Only he was a gardener chauffeur - in the end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did he live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No, he lived in a - little cottage - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 bungalow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  thing down the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they make any homemade wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. They never did, they bought that enough. They had to buy th
eirs but - they knew a - and they knew a - man somewhere in Covent Garden who could get a - oh a lot of - any amount of sugar, when nobody else could get any, but he could always get - he could get no end. There was - hundred - hundred - hundred weight I 
suppose they were. Yellow crystals, demarara, caster, granulated, all these sort of - loaf.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So they had a few contacts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes they did, and I mean they were up on the - by being a three storey they were up on - right on the top where nobody probabl
y would never go up. But they kept that - they kept the loaf sugar in a - attic. And - and we - there was a - they had a freeze up, you know, a tank froze up and this - old fellow, he used to do the estate work then, he wasn't really estate man but he use
d to do - and he went up there. He saw the sugar. I don't know how many times he didn't come down - we wondered why he kept coming down so many times, but - he filled his pockets each time with the sugar - with the sugar, loaf sugar.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did the gardener }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 grow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  enough vegetables and things to keep the house going, or was it mainly flowers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Oh - oh no. No, not - not - big flowers or anything like - used to grow little ones of course. Oh they used to grow most of the - vegetables, spinach and stuff like that, and I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 didn\rquote t}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  like spinach - either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they use much tinned or dried vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Not dried vegetables, there wasn't them then. They'd got some other tins stuff, you know, like - oh, what is called - caf\'e9
 au lait and - all stuff lik
e that. Then they got to a stage where they - they said somebody was going to come round and - have a look see what she'd got, see if you'd got more than what you should got - should have got. And - they buried theirs in a hole in the garden, but of cours
e they come - they got rusty tins and that weren't much good in it like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they keep any livestock there, any hens or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No not there, no. But they had a - they had a few - they used to keep a few in a - an old barn down th
e bottom of the road. And there was a boy that used to - quite a young lad, and he collected up these - eggs, and he brought in a - one of those galvanized bowls, you know, with a handle. He brought 'em to the door, and he didn't say mind the handle. And 
my sister got hold of it and of course that went down like that and all the eggs went out - oh - oh all the eggs went down on the doorstep. And he laughed, of course he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have meat most days at this place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We always had one meatless da
y. I didn't know what day it was but there was always one meatless day. We - we had other - I don't know quite what we had on say - lentils pea soup and - stuff like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they ever take you away on holiday with them or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well - I say she had a - she had a - they had a cottage at Great Holland. And - they used to go there with her. Sometimes we'd go for a week. But - I'd have to go back with him so that he could run his business, and the other one was - the other one st
ayed there so - I had to do - and I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you enjoy these breaks, this week away?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes I - yes, I used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they seem any different on holiday than at home, were they any easier with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well it was all the - I - we used to go and take - have a picnic and they used to come and have a picnic out with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you had a fairly friendly relationship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes we did, have a fairly - you know, nice - fairly friendly atmosphere there was to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were there any other occasions at all or was there just this one week a year you used to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well we used to have our own holiday. We had our own holiday and then she'd - occasionally she'd - take us up to London - somewhere sort of - you know - take us all round the different places, where we wouldn't ever have got. There was some quite -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You mean like the Tower of London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes we did. We'd go in Selfridges and - have our meal in there. I always remember - to start off we had - we had white bait, she said, you eat it with your fingers. Yes. Oh we had a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So they taught you quite a lot really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, they did. Oh yes they did, that gives you - give you a good start for yourself you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did the master or mistress think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
There was nothing much going on there. He was getting on. He used to go church practically every Sunday. That was only just around the corner but - he'd always go to church on Sundays. Sometimes she would. But latterly
 she wouldn't be in very good health so she - she just couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you used to attend the same church as them or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - I was - married in that church. Yes, I was married in there - in that - that was only like a - Hutton Union church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you used to go with them or on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh we usually went on our - on our own. I mean, we couldn't leave together. When we went we sat at the back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Was grace said at meals in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh in there. In there it was. Yes. Yes, that was different there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you used to have family -prayers there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
I don't know what - I can't remember whether - he had - whether they had prayers or not. I think somehow - oh no, that wasn't there, I think - there was a place 
where I went - and I stayed with - when my sister lived at Mundon - the two women were sisters, and he always had prayers. Night and morning. Mr Knowle his name was. And we all had to go in, you know, and have prayers there. But I don't think they did the
re - particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What denomination were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I suppose you'd say they're church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your master or mistress take any interest in politics at all do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - she might probably - she did but - not too much of the politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you know what her politics were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, I don't know, I wouldn't know - he was a J.P., that's all I can see. Yes, he was a J.P.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did he take any interest in any sports or go to the races or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No. No, they just didn't go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 He didn't go to a club or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No, there was no clubs, I mean if they went out they went out together. They just went to visit a few friends but I mean they didn't stay out to long. They would go - what was that - they 
went to a drill hall and they had something there, they had something on, Gilbert and Sullivan. They had the whole season for that so they used to go - they used to go to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did the mistress have any interests outside the home, did she sit on any committees or do work with charities or anything like this?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No, I can't think that she did. Sometimes - she was asked sometimes to - go and speak at different things. 'Cos I say, she was a matron in a hospital and - you know, they went and asked her about - different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So she'd be quite busy, she'd be at work most days would she?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. Not - not as work as such. No. Not - not work as such.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How many days would she be out at the hospital then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, she didn't go out after she was married. No, she didn't go out after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did your master's occupation ever take him away from home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No. He only went to the gate you know where he'd got his business to do. Well - the - I'm sorry, it did. He - went to Germany to buy his ma
chinery. And that - he'd got some money left - oh I don't know, fifty pfenigs, I don't think that was only about a farthing or something like that and he gave us all the money when he came back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would this be after 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, that only started up
 but he was going to start up again. He got the machinery before then. You - you got to have the machinery before you can start up. Yes. So that was the only time that used to take him away. But if they - they - sometimes they'd go for a - a week - only a
 weekend. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 You know, and go down to a friend's home, I knew the people. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
They'd go down there, and I remember he - I shouldn't think too much of it really. He bought - a bundle of safety pins and some old little tiny pins on a cushion. There you are girls, he said, now you can pin yourself up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 They'd just leave you at home then would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Yes, they used to leave us at home. Yes, so I mean we'd got a - that was a big - you know, a responsibility and I know - one night when they went away 'cos - ther
e was one room she used to lock up, 'cos there was a lot of things in there, she used to lock that. That was close to our bedroom. There was such a commotion, I said, well what - ever on earth is it? But it was some - something that had - oh, the toilet w
as next to it so I opened the window quick, I thought well if it's anybody with a ladder - I can - probably push 'em off. But it was something fell down in - a lot of books come }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 sliding}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  down I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they have friends come and stay with them very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh they - yes, they used to have friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Stay overnight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, they - they'd come and stay for a - come and stay for a week or something like that - at times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What kind of people were these friends, what sort of class were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well there was - some of those - I mean - somewhere on their own level where they think they could employ somebody. But - there was one or two of 'em, they were - nicer - with her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Her old friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Her old friends, they used to come. Their children you see, used - they used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would you say the master and mistress were both from the same class of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, I should imagine so. Well - she didn't mind but - I mean, he was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 
brick maker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  as - a brick manufacturer. He was that. She was a little bit better I think, she was some relation of Lord Mayor of London - at one time. Bowater.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So she was higher up than him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 She was a little bit higher but she wanted to go in for nursing and her - father cut her right off w
ithout a penny, but she still - she still went in for it. So - consequently that made her - well, get married late in life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you think they showed different respect to their friends, would they put on a posher meal for some than others or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
No, I don't think she - but if she had anybody in for a meal she - she'd - there'd probably be a little bit more you know, another course or something like that. But for the special occasion but she - didn't make too much distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did the guests treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh quite all right, they used to tip us at the end and that's what we liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 So you quite looked forward to visitors coming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. We used to get a tip at the end. That swelled the money up a little bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did all the guests treat you the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well - I don't know whether they all paid the same sort of money but - you know, yes, for services rendered really. I mean there was a lot to do, I mean, you'd - water and everything to take upstairs and - and all everything el
se, beds to turn down and - all things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were the friends as friendly as the master and mistress were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes, more or less, yes, they didn't - they didn't make much - you were still the maid but I mean they didn't make all that distinction.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 It was still a fairly friendly sort of basis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Do you think that the master and mistress were content with their station in life, or do you think they would have liked to have been a bit higher up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, they seemed quite all right. Yes. I mean they'd got enough money to go on with so - and they accepted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Had you met people from this sort of level in life before you left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh well, there - there wasn't any. I mean there wasn't anybody that we - when we
 were at home there was nobody there. I said the only person who - who really thought he was anything at all was the parson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did you think of these people and their way of living, did it strike you as very different from your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh
 - that is, that's really - you know, it really is - good, I mean you - learnt to do the things that - well how they should be done then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you think their manners and general behaviour seemed different from people you'd associated with before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Oh yes, oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 In what ways would you say particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well good manners, most of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You stayed at this place until 1924 when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I went there in 19 - 1916. And I stayed there 'til 1924.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Have you worked since you were married? Not until you you're your husband, when was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 1948.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well I - didn't do anything, sort of - I'd got too much work to do here. Not here but down there. I worked like a Trojan then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Looking after your house and garden?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well yes. Well I mean that was a big - that was a big garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Would you have preferred any other sort of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No I don't think so. No, I don't - I don't think I would. I mean it was hard, but
 I - I still got - and even now I mean if I hadn't got a bit of garden I'd be lost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you belong to any trade union or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. That wasn't work like that you see. The only thing I used to - the only thing I used to - I had to fire watch 
when - he used to work nights at times. And while he was at work I had to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 fire watch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754  - fire work on me own premises.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Do you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Well - they - they vary you see, they change. They c
hange such a lot. Yes. I mean, you may just - you've only go to do - well I say, but that wasn't - up to 18 - 19 - 1918 I mean that was all before that but - we had to - I was doing the firewatching - fire work, watching we - took a doodlebug. They came -
 
they came down on me very sudden. They wouldn't come down on London, they suddenly - this was - with the doodlebug days. Somebody said, well we're coming down to - we're making a big effort to come down to you. So they - they came. Well there was a big ra
id that night and did she kick up - a storm. Oh, I said, wherever were you? She said, well I got in a room somewhere and I couldn't get out. And - the flat had took a bomb.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You didn't live at home after you left school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. I never - I ne
ver had a - I never had a chance - after sixteen I never had a chance. There wasn't a home. About thirteen and a half, when I had - I'd got to have so many stamps you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you see much of your sisters at all after you left school, you had one work
ing with you, the others had to go out to work as they got old enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well - well - the - but the - the three that I showed you there, they weren't very old. I mean, she was up above me, well of course she was - she was at work, I used to see her oc
casionally if we got a visit. That's right, we - it's very difficult to - get the other people - to understand that - it was your sister and - you wanted to see them. And - they'd still got to be very careful. There were - I wouldn't say mistrusting you, 
b
ut they were putting you on your honour, the whole time. So you lived a life of - being on your honour. Put it like that. And - we couldn't get the same days off. No, so it was very difficult. Very difficult like that. And that's really why - we didn't - 
we weren't able to see - it - it's a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 terrific}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
 sacrifice when you look back on it. Yes, I mean, we lost - we lost touch with some. Oh one - one sister now, we don't know whether she was bombed, whether she's here anywhere or whether she - she used to live at
 Tottenham somewhere but - whether she's still here or not I - I - I don't know. But I'm just wondering how old she'd be.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you take any interest in politics at all before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No. None at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you make any new friends at this time? While you were in service before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well - there wasn't time to meet - very many. I mean - we'd go off - on our evenings out we'd go to the pictures and - then you walk home again. You get there and then you walk home again. But I mean, y
ou'd be - could - you had to be careful because if they heard anything pull up - when you're supposed to be there - they'd want to - they'd soon be there wanting to know who was this you come home with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Who did you used to go with to the pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Alone. Yes, used to go on our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Were you allowed to bring friends back }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 at all}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No. There was no followers. - NA.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did you have any special friends at this time, boyfriends or girlfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 You would just more or less go out on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Well just - if we went out if there was a - a fete or something, in the end, my sister and I. We used to go out. I mean - we could go together then. But I had - never got - they expected us to be in at the same time, only thin
g if we'd gone to the pictures - they knew they didn't come - you - couldn't get out time enough you see. They didn't close to a certain time. They - yes, they'd allowed you 'til half past nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did they expect to know where you were going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 No, 
they didn't ask - they didn't ask you where you were going but if they - I say, if they heard a car pull up outside they were soon there as to know - where you had been. Who you'd been with or something like that, I mean - you really couldn't accept a lif
t home because, oh you'd get your head - knocked off.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Who was the family breadwinner after your father died in 1909?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 My mother was the breadwinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Did she earn enough to keep the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I do not think that it was enough, but there 
was no more forthcoming, except the 5/- parish relief so she had to manage. It was cheaper to live in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 What did she work at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 A little bit of charring, and took in washing in spite of having to fetch the water from the pond; in the fie
lds at harvest time and pea-picking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Your mother's brother still lived with you at the time. Did he keep the family - or just pay his own keep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 He just paid for himself, with a gold sovereign. He bought the seed potatoes cabbage, etc., and did the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 How did you manage when she was ill? Did anyone help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
Luckily, my mother, apart from the odd headache, was not ill. This was the country with very few neighbours around, so if she had the odd day or two off colour we all had to do our share and help, we were very lucky that way and I thank God for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15024670 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 Please add any comments or information you think may be useful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 I went into service at the age of 14 and that eased the situation a little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 During the summer months w
e fetched the milk from a nearby farm for which we 1/2d per pint, 1d quart, etc., etc., this we did twice a day. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4591158\charrsid15539754 
At the end of the week it was 'totted' up, we got something for ourselves and my mother had the rest, it was not enough of course, but we never
 went hungry and touch wood we were not ill in the ill sense just 'measles', 'chicken pox' and the tooth ache, I cannot ever remember the doctor having to call.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13070006 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537365\charrsid15539754 We each wore a necklace of beads around our necks, never took them off. If they broke the
y were hastily threaded on string and put back again, superstition maybe but it seemed to work.
